<graph edgedefault="undirected"><node id="Cuba">
  <data key="d0">Cuba</data>
  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">Cuba is a country where protests are taking place, accompanied by arson, and where a prolonged power outage has occurred. entity United States country United States is a country with which the president of Cuba has announced the beginning of negotiations. entity Communist Party of Cuba organization Communist Party of Cuba is a political organization whose local offices have been set on fire by rioters in some cities. entity President person President is a person who announced the beginning of negotiations with the United States, which served as an additional catalyst for protests. relation Cuba United States negotiation,diplomatic engagement The president of Cuba announced the beginning of negotiations with the United States, which triggered further protests. relation Cuba Communist Party of Cuba targeted,attack Rioters in some cities set fire to local offices of the Communist Party of Cuba during the protests. relation President Communist Party of Cuba leadership,association The president of Cuba is the head of state associated with the Communist Party of Cuba, which was targeted during the protests. relation Cuba President governance,leadership The president leads Cuba and made a public announcement that influenced the escalation of protests.&lt;SEP&gt;Cuba is a country subject to a U.S. energy blockade and is the destination of Russian oil shipments, as described in the text.&lt;SEP&gt;Cuba is a country that receives oil from nations targeted by tariffs signed by Donald Trump.&lt;SEP&gt;Cuba is a country that held secret talks with the United States in Havana, with its government accused of allowing foreign intelligence, military, and terrorist groups to operate near U.S. territory.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3d31f0e0677eda8305196001171ef666&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9ebb3ed519c434b35de7bc7a410af22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-12870e1307e69d66c099b1b0c3b44383&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07e1a126d8b8691b4020263f5c90fd4b</data>
