  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="State Department">
  <data key="d0">State Department</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">State Department is a U.S. government diplomatic agency that led a delegation to Havana for secret negotiations with Cuban authorities and presented demands regarding economic reforms, political prisoners, and asset compensation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-07e1a126d8b8691b4020263f5c90fd4b</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Куба\8.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777598356</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Starlink">
  <data key="d0">Starlink</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Starlink is a satellite communication system offered by the United States as part of a proposal to Cuba in exchange for political and economic reforms.&lt;SEP&gt;Starlink is a satellite internet service used by Russian drone operators for command and control, whose disconnection has significantly degraded Russian tactical communication and drone effectiveness.&lt;SEP&gt;Starlink is a satellite internet service provided by SpaceX that Russian military forces used for high-precision drone strikes, real-time video transmission, and battlefield communication, until its access was cut off.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-07e1a126d8b8691b4020263f5c90fd4b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cef941579131f01cafedf58b7d330624&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba68be1ab3264024852e59eb0966356d</data>
