<node id="Germany">
  <data key="d0">Germany</data>
  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">Germany is the Federal Republic of Germany, a European nation represented by the flag emoji 🇩🇪, where complex political, historical, and security dynamics intersect. Public opinion on Ukraine is divided, with a poll indicating that 52% of respondents support increased Western assistance to Ukraine, while 35% oppose further support, reflecting broader debates over the deployment of Bundeswehr soldiers to the region. The country is home to the far-right Alternative for Germany (AfD), a political party active at the federal level in the Bundestag and in regional governments such as Saxony-Anhalt and Baden-Württemberg. AfD’s political stance has drawn criticism for its close alignment with Russia, prompting party members to distance themselves from Donald Trump’s aggressive policies to avoid association with his rhetoric. Germany is also a site of ongoing far-right extremist activity, including the presence and influence of the Atomwaffen Division and the Terrorgram network, with 37 cases of extremist plots identified and prevented between the pandemic and 2025. Historically, Germany is inextricably linked to the rise of Nazi ideology, including key figures such as Adolf Hitler and Johann von Leers, and remains a focal point in analyses of post-war neo-Nazi Islamism and the legacy of far-right extremism in Europe. The current Chancellor, Merz, presides over a political landscape shaped by these enduring tensions between democratic governance and resurgent nationalist movements.&lt;SEP&gt;Germany is a NATO member state that operates the Pegasus aircraft for signals intelligence.&lt;SEP&gt;Германия is implicitly referenced through the phrase "немецкими женщинами," indicating German influence over European nations.&lt;SEP&gt;Germany is a country whose chancellor is cited by Viktor Orbán as maintaining sanctions on Russian oil, contributing to high fuel prices in Europe.&lt;SEP&gt;Germany is a European Union member state that opposes the accelerated accession of Ukraine to the European Union and has engaged in diplomatic outreach to Russia regarding potential negotiations.&lt;SEP&gt;Germany is a European country led by Markus Söder, with whom Keir Starmer coordinates on defense and security strategy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1ee2064130371330ef4a5652dba192c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8109eafe35c828056622b31d32cb9a3b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ed06713c000461ec66858856eef1a63&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b328e8d4304c0d0b1c17749a4f9e42bf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-52970e012540831e77e393d5b4e7bd3f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-786e4ab2b6966bcfcf341c317a1d4e1c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bdde8f24aa613c9ae76329db019d6d7a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c0e45973e2056f2a0c6c6cf9df17553&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d8dc136c80cd91ef2cf9ad9756a4d52&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a2d5e0f3941015b9813c436f7443def&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f3dc55aad4eb94544269bbfd9dec2905&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3117b3a03ff471f00f67b26aade3e091&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-adcce0ecbb12090a19fa597edabfada4</data>
