<node id="AfD">
  <data key="d0">AfD</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">AfD (Alternative for Germany) is a far-right German political party known for its strong opposition to Western involvement in the Ukraine conflict, with 65% of its voters firmly rejecting any military or financial assistance to Ukraine. The party advocates for peace talks between Ukraine and Russia and opposes Western interference in diplomatic processes. It is led by Алиса Вайдель (Alice Waidel), though some sources reference slight variations in the spelling of her name. AfD has internal factions, with prominent figures such as Matthias Mözdorf and Björn Höcke associated with its pro-Russian line, while Marcus Frontmeyer is politically aligned with the party. The party has been implicated in multiple scandals, including allegations of nepotism at both regional and federal levels, despite positioning itself as a critic of “party nepotism.” It is also suspected of transmitting classified European Union documents to Russia. Furthermore, some members of AfD have been identified among individuals arrested in connection with Atomwaffen Division activities, raising concerns about links to extremist networks. These multiple dimensions—political ideology, leadership structure, alleged misconduct, and extremist affiliations—paint a complex portrait of AfD as a controversial and ideologically driven force within German politics.&lt;SEP&gt;AfD is the Alternative for Germany party, led by Alice Weidel, which is ideologically aligned with Viktor Orbán and Fidesz.&lt;SEP&gt;AfD is not mentioned in the text; no entity extracted.&lt;SEP&gt;AfD is not mentioned in the input text; no correction needed.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1ee2064130371330ef4a5652dba192c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed3f829c79f231e6cf23a14022015c5c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ed06713c000461ec66858856eef1a63&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b328e8d4304c0d0b1c17749a4f9e42bf&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-74413fdb4ad3f1b0bd542a794fe97eaa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a74d8a7ca84ed003e119ba5cde1f80dc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bdde8f24aa613c9ae76329db019d6d7a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c748c9a23ba05cffbc5245984ffc52e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-aeeb3e654a660cb7b38dfc9d61222bc9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0db27d1e5bd672959a82744488e5a07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-17e8350a36758c6e44f8b72ee0cd6731</data>
