<node id="The Left">
  <data key="d0">The Left</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Left is a political party in Germany whose supporters most strongly oppose the idea of deploying Bundeswehr soldiers to Ukraine.&lt;SEP&gt;The Left is a far-left political faction in the European Parliament that criticizes Ursula von der Leyen for supporting neoliberal capitalism, militarization, and corporate interests.&lt;SEP&gt;The Left is a political group in the European Parliament that initiated a motion of censure in October 2025 against the European Commission.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1ee2064130371330ef4a5652dba192c2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e8f1d70c706294695eca41aa0252d062&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a73e41ce47973ce6d0501f8f7acc0955</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\3.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\20.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\21.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777598734</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vladimir Putin">
  <data key="d0">Vladimir Putin</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Vladimir Putin is the President of Russia and the country’s dominant political leader, widely recognized for his central role in shaping Russia’s domestic and foreign policies. He has openly articulated goals related to the so-called special military operation (SVO) in Ukraine, aiming to expand Russia’s security buffer zone, influence European politics by supporting ultranationalist and far-left populist movements, and undermine NATO’s presence, which he views as an existential threat. Putin has been accused by multiple sources of violating international law and committing war crimes, particularly in connection with the invasion of Ukraine across its internationally recognized border. His leadership has drawn comparisons and alliances with several European political figures, notably Hungary’s Prime Minister Viktor Orbán, who regards Putin as an ideological model and has forged deep economic and diplomatic ties with Russia, exemplified by the Paks II nuclear power plant agreement. Putin maintains direct personal contact with Orbán, including calling him on his birthday, and the two have discussed strengthening their alliance against common opponents, with Orbán pledging loyalty and assistance. Their relationship is implied to be motivated by mutual benefit, including political alignment and potential asset concealment. Putin has also been described as a close friend of Slovakia’s leadership, with assurances that he has no intention to attack Slovakia, while simultaneously being referenced by Peter Magyar as a potential eastern threat to Hungary alongside Volodymyr Zelensky. His political influence extends to perceived alignments with Donald Trump’s policies, and his decisions on energy have sparked intense debate over European sanctions. Putin is portrayed in some texts as the mastermind behind a tightly controlled inner circle of associates, some referred to with derogatory nicknames such as “cook,” “violinist,” and “purses.” Additionally, Putin is accused of providing specific and dangerous support to North Korea in exchange for military personnel deployed in Ukraine. Described by some as a bloodthirsty dictator waging war, and by others as a strategic realist, Putin remains a pivotal and controversial figure in global geopolitics, predicted by some to dismantle international stability if not opposed.&lt;SEP&gt;Vladimir Putin is a political figure whose actions in other parts of the world are cited as causing fluctuations in energy bills.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-965b8760e7f023cb5fe999d79e061c32&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed3f829c79f231e6cf23a14022015c5c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0db27d1e5bd672959a82744488e5a07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2025a50f1328b82f061a4942a8dd453&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2ed677b91cd8a20441c02fa69439eac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30533205f101cc1df47f96e15592f2b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aedd80ca30611f4314d3afe2ee2ad0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-02f8127f57647c6f52ac2f580f293f65&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3aab01d8a12e8135d55b3153fc006d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bd0a283b39238236a064e8afb069c87&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de92df91fd68b8019a5e2c98e87d545e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2369463d8ede9e477cfaf832815ef3c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1704b3bc09f596547c35a95941e29e5f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dc8a59662338ae99506795bdf8f3e570&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bba75e995cd78b326b3a8504ee463aff</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\4.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\8.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\13.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\50.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\92.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\110.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\123.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\131.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\142.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\149.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Корея\25.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Англия\9.txt</data>
