<node id="Other">
  <data key="d0">Other</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">The term "ультра-левые" refers to ultra-left groups, and "ультра-правые" refers to ultra-right groups, both of which are ideological movements described as aligning in the source text.&lt;SEP&gt;Unspecified criminal organization referred to as "мафия" (mafia) that was expelled from the country. entity Other other Unspecified country from which the criminal organization was expelled. relation Other Other expulsion,criminal_activity A criminal organization referred to as "мафия" was expelled from a country due to its crimes, while illicit funds associated with it were not removed, suggesting they are no longer considered illicit.&lt;SEP&gt;A person with disabilities and diabetes, detained in Budapest, was denied necessary medications and special nutrition, lost consciousness, and was forcibly administered a drug causing a sharp rise in blood sugar and hypertensive reaction.&lt;SEP&gt;The text contains personal, emotional communication but no other identifiable entities fitting the provided types.&lt;SEP&gt;The term "mouse" is used as a derogatory metaphor in the text to describe Viktor Orbán’s perceived subservience to Vladimir Putin.</data>
