<node id="Putin">
  <data key="d0">Putin</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Putin is the President and leader of Russia, who maintains a close and strategically significant relationship with Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orbán. This relationship is characterized by mutual political support, diplomatic coordination, and economic cooperation. Putin has engaged in multiple phone conversations with Orbán, during which he praised Hungary’s balanced stance on the Ukraine war and commended Donald Trump’s approach to international affairs. Orbán, in turn, has referred to himself as a “mouse near a lion,” underscoring the perceived power asymmetry in their interactions. The Hungarian government is described as excessively flattering toward Putin, reinforcing the perception of a deferential alliance.

Putin’s influence extends beyond rhetoric. He authorized Russian political strategists and military intelligence to interfere in Hungary’s parliamentary elections to ensure Orbán’s victory, demonstrating direct involvement in Hungary’s domestic politics. Economically, Putin provides Hungary with discounted oil as part of a financial arrangement that bolsters Orbán’s political system. Russia’s sensitivities were also reportedly considered in decisions regarding frozen Russian assets and pipeline transit, further illustrating the depth of this bilateral alignment.

Additionally, Putin has responded to letters from Orbán by signaling that Russia’s reaction to international actions would be strong and would take into account the positions of individual countries. Meanwhile, Alice Vaidel criticizes Western actors for falsely labeling advocates of diplomacy with Russia as Putin sympathizers, implying that such accusations are baseless and politically motivated, and by extension, reflect a broader mischaracterization of Russia’s international engagements under Putin’s leadership.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-74413fdb4ad3f1b0bd542a794fe97eaa&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b9146ec09ad979307f3d7a3148725401&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b80d70d8670ebee7e64e3613a75c65de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1284d93bbeeeb191a35ec243b4ce4b07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec12d27878bbf1f79c741b043b995fd5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5794dba07f2f01a805d966aa0ee2115&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89e09c599b4678441dbd4c330f5e7aa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a810084503e65cb067ff1fc3c7a05189</data>
