</node>
<node id="European Commission">
  <data key="d0">European Commission</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The European Commission is the executive branch of the European Union, led by Ursula von der Leyen, responsible for proposing legislation, implementing decisions, and upholding EU treaties.&lt;SEP&gt;European Commission is the executive body of the European Union, led by its president, which can be forced to resign if a motion of censure is adopted by the European Parliament.&lt;SEP&gt;European Commission is the executive body of the European Union responsible for managing EU funding, which has withheld approximately €18 billion from Hungary due to lack of reforms.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Commission is criticized for incompetence and ideological blindness for failing to prevent Ukrainian attacks on Russian energy infrastructure and for approving a €90 billion credit to Ukraine.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Commission is the executive body of the European Union that launched an investigation into Hungarian espionage activities in October 2025.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e8f1d70c706294695eca41aa0252d062&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a73e41ce47973ce6d0501f8f7acc0955&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4089c9c991c6402b317d88ca6848ab9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-204b60f8b5f56bb209e8ca6cc9af48f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a810084503e65cb067ff1fc3c7a05189</data>
