</node>
<node id="Atomwaffen Division">
  <data key="d0">Atomwaffen Division</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Atomwaffen Division is a transnational, decentralized neo-Nazi network inspired by white supremacy, partially blending it with concepts of "Salafist national socialism" and "white jihad." It supports Hamas, Al-Qaeda, and ISIS, operates through a fragmented structure of isolated groups and lone actors, and promotes militant accelerationism to destabilize democratic societies through violence and chaos. It emulates jihadist media practices, including the cult of "martyrs" (called "Saints"), propaganda via memes and manifestos, and the "lone actor" strategy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bdde8f24aa613c9ae76329db019d6d7a</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\22.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777598878</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hamas">
  <data key="d0">Hamas</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Hamas is a jihadist organization supported by Atomwaffen Division and referenced as a shared ideological enemy of liberal democracies within the Terrorgram scene.&lt;SEP&gt;Hamas is a Palestinian Islamist organization that published and distributed David Myatt’s writings, recognizing him as an authoritative Islamist voice.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-bdde8f24aa613c9ae76329db019d6d7a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c0e45973e2056f2a0c6c6cf9df17553</data>
