<node id="Robert Fico">
  <data key="d0">Robert Fico</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Robert Fico is the Prime Minister of Slovakia, a self-described leftist socialist politician who returned to lead the SMER party in 2023 and has since formed a government coalition that includes ultraright, anti-Ukrainian forces. Fico has adopted a staunchly anti-Western stance on Ukraine, opposing Western military support—including blocking the transfer of MiG-29 fighters and diesel fuel exports—while justifying these actions as necessary for Slovakia’s national defense, despite having previously ordered F-16 fighter jet replacements in 2018. He has publicly rejected the 20th package of EU sanctions against Russia and criticized the European Union and Ukraine for actions affecting energy infrastructure, while refusing to participate in a proposed €90 billion EU aid package for Ukraine. Fico has dismissed as “nonsense” the idea that the war in Ukraine will weaken Russia and has been accused of enabling Kremlin influence, including allegations of involvement in efforts to sway Slovak elections and benefiting from a manufactured migration crisis orchestrated by Hungary’s Viktor Orbán. His government has drawn scrutiny for ceasing emergency electricity supplies to Ukraine following a Russian attack on the Druzhba pipeline, prompting an investigation into possible treason and abuse of power. Fico has also sought alternative diplomatic routes to Moscow, after Lithuania and Latvia denied his plane overflight permissions, and later requested permission from Poland to fly to a May 9 parade in Moscow, echoing a similar incident with Estonia the prior year. He is accused of manipulating Slovakia’s electoral code to consolidate power amid declining approval ratings and the threat of early elections or a referendum. Additionally, his administration has been linked to the Epstein files through correspondence. Critics compare Fico to Orbán, viewing him as part of a broader Central European bloc resisting Western unity on Ukraine, and anticipate he will continue obstructing EU solidarity efforts even if Orbán’s influence diminishes.&lt;SEP&gt;Robert Fico is the Slovak prime minister who seeks to visit the Kremlin, particularly on May 9, and has faced diplomatic resistance from Estonia, Lithuania, Latvia, and Poland. He is perceived as a "mini-Orbán" and has previously blocked EU sanctions, though he recently refrained from blocking the 20th sanctions package. His political position is unstable amid domestic protests and potential early elections.&lt;SEP&gt;Robert Fico is the Prime Minister of Slovakia who held negotiations with President Zelensky and expressed interest in strengthening bilateral relations and sharing Euro-integration experience.&lt;SEP&gt;Robert Fico is the Prime Minister of Slovakia who supported Ukraine's accession to the European Union and is scheduled to visit Moscow on May 9, maintaining a pro-Russian alignment.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1b86c9560ec7e43e68be30c2e38dbbde&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-11b9d96fc698fa7b9242168a7bad3295&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d0db27d1e5bd672959a82744488e5a07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-43d54b3b9775efd5f7d0080cad36c2de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8f6038412dae5ce5c36860aae0893cce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0b9d4541f93fbe1abbecc6f52128db7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a55a1b2f7d86f155201f7562a7195495&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0d2e8519cd0bab60a3e52b70a90d3f0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7fe37316c34f12bcbc2eaa45277e7b90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-204b60f8b5f56bb209e8ca6cc9af48f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-09de750ab096b64385f95a95c7d0e5ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cab9a94ea286a7616cc63009e8c3d5ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-313fbd5b1968d3d281c042524d458b06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81f9a312226a282bf8ebf1aee5ad788a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9bcca043358a8f1b8a9a2999a79a6f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac57a8e21b0821ebfc4b7007fb6688a3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-116374b92e94e5c9f902ad74ec9408ea</data>
