</node>
<node id="Moscow">
  <data key="d0">Moscow</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Moscow is the capital of Russia and serves as the central hub of Russian political, diplomatic, and intelligence operations that actively cultivate influence in Hungary and other European states. It is the location of key diplomatic infrastructure, including the Hungarian embassy, and has been the site of high-level negotiations between Russian and Hungarian officials, particularly prior to the signing of agreements under Hungary’s Prime Minister Orbán, whose political decisions are closely aligned with Moscow’s interests. Moscow also features in strategic communications: Siyarto made calls from EU meetings to Moscow to relay negotiation details, and the city is associated with plans for information campaigns targeting Hungarian leadership. Additionally, Moscow hosts the Gnessin Academy of Music, where Matthias Mözdorf holds the title of honorary professor. The city is further linked to broader geopolitical alliances, notably Russia’s longstanding political ties with Iran. These varied roles—cultural, diplomatic, intelligence, and strategic—underscore Moscow’s multifaceted significance as both a national capital and a node of transnational influence.&lt;SEP&gt;Moscow is the destination Robert Fico intended to reach, which is blocked by the refusal of Lithuania and Latvia to permit overflight.&lt;SEP&gt;Moscow is the destination city where a parade is scheduled for May 9, which Robert Fico intends to attend.&lt;SEP&gt;Moscow is the capital of Russia and the destination of Robert Fico's planned visit on May 9.&lt;SEP&gt;Moscow is the capital of Russia and represents the Russian government in its deepening cooperation with Pyongyang.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c748c9a23ba05cffbc5245984ffc52e3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-00452022e84a0076582b1330b967245d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba1043e375054a4f318c66342ee9ad31&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1d17587159dea209c75a0ae5875a4b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9360bf859acb934b8ebad024d1c18290&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bd0a283b39238236a064e8afb069c87&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f7b78146485b6ecfc5184d01e665fc8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-35ef5418fbb73e10428a076cc8117782&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-313fbd5b1968d3d281c042524d458b06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81f9a312226a282bf8ebf1aee5ad788a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-116374b92e94e5c9f902ad74ec9408ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dc8a59662338ae99506795bdf8f3e570</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\27.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\87.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\97.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\135.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\136.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\143.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\160.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\196.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\197.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\202.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Корея\25.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777938928</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Narva">
  <data key="d0">Narva</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Narva is a city in Estonia that Russian propagandists propose to capture to undermine European and NATO political resolve.&lt;SEP&gt;Narva is a city in Estonia that Russia may target for capture as part of a limited invasion scenario.&lt;SEP&gt;Narva is a city in Estonia mentioned as a location where separatist ideas are being spread, allegedly as part of a Russian strategy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-691db0c7da6c565b77c4361c38ccf0cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a126839f1ff6597735159d84aa24a61&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65cd56937cfc8cc228d0f1e651ee3abe</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\4.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\6.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\2.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1778011207</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
  <data key="d7">Narva</data>
</node>
<node id="Estonia">
  <data key="d0">Estonia</data>
  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">Estonia is a country whose city, Narva, is targeted for capture according to Russian propagandists.&lt;SEP&gt;Estonia is a Baltic State where Russia is allegedly spreading propaganda about the persecution of Russian-speaking populations to justify potential military action.&lt;SEP&gt;Estonia is a country that previously blocked Robert Fico's overflight, as referenced in his statement.&lt;SEP&gt;Estonia is a Baltic country that joined Lithuania and Latvia in denying Robert Fico permission to fly through its territory to reach Moscow.&lt;SEP&gt;Estonia is a Baltic nation that refused to allow Robert Fico’s aircraft to transit its airspace, signaling opposition to his pro-Kremlin overtures.&lt;SEP&gt;Estonia is a country targeted by alleged Russian separatist activities in Narva and Ida-Viru County, and is considered a potential victim of Russian invasion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-691db0c7da6c565b77c4361c38ccf0cb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1a126839f1ff6597735159d84aa24a61&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-313fbd5b1968d3d281c042524d458b06&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81f9a312226a282bf8ebf1aee5ad788a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9bcca043358a8f1b8a9a2999a79a6f6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-65cd56937cfc8cc228d0f1e651ee3abe</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\4.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\6.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\196.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\197.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\198.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\2.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1778011207</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
  <data key="d7">Estonia</data>
</node>
<node id="Михаил Фёдоров">
  <data key="d0">Михаил Фёдоров</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Михаил Фёдоров is the new Minister of Defense of Ukraine, whose appointment is associated with a significant increase in the number of Ukrainian drone units and improved drone operations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cef941579131f01cafedf58b7d330624</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\3.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777932678</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ВСУ">
  <data key="d0">ВСУ</data>
  <data key="d1">military_unit</data>
  <data key="d2">ВСУ (Armed Forces of Ukraine) is the military force that has regained dominance in the use of FPV drones, employs advanced signals intelligence capabilities, and targets Russian drone operators through radio signal detection and interception.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cef941579131f01cafedf58b7d330624</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\3.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777932678</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Российские дроноводы">
  <data key="d0">Российские дроноводы</data>
  <data key="d1">military_unit</data>
  <data key="d2">Russian drone operators are military personnel who rely on Starlink and radio communication for drone control, and have experienced reduced effectiveness due to the cutoff of Starlink and increased Ukrainian electronic warfare capabilities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cef941579131f01cafedf58b7d330624</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\3.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777932678</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Филатов">
  <data key="d0">Филатов</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Филатов is a military correspondent (Военкор) who reports on Ukrainian dominance in FPV drone operations and the tactical shift in Ukrainian drone tactics.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cef941579131f01cafedf58b7d330624</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\3.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777932678</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Старше Эды">
  <data key="d0">Старше Эды</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Старше Эды is a popular Z-channel that highlights the critical importance of Starlink connectivity for Russian drone operations and the consequences of its loss.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cef941579131f01cafedf58b7d330624</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\3.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777932678</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Разведос">
  <data key="d0">Разведос</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Разведос is a Russian military intelligence officer who participated in Russia’s military operations in Ukraine and reported on the failure of Canadian electronic warfare systems due to outdated firmware.&lt;SEP&gt;Разведос is a military commentator who observes and reports on the systematic targeting of Russian drone operator teams by Ukrainian forces following the detection of their radio signals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cef941579131f01cafedf58b7d330624&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7d8dc136c80cd91ef2cf9ad9756a4d52</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\3.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777932678</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="FPV-дроны">
  <data key="d0">FPV-дроны</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">FPV-дроны (First-Person View drones) are unmanned aerial vehicles used for reconnaissance and strike missions, which Ukrainian forces have increasingly dominated in use due to improved communication and operational tactics.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cef941579131f01cafedf58b7d330624</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\3.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777932678</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Радиотехническая разведка ВСУ">
  <data key="d0">Радиотехническая разведка ВСУ</data>
  <data key="d1">military_unit</data>
  <data key="d2">Радиотехническая разведка ВСУ (Signals Intelligence units of the Armed Forces of Ukraine) are specialized units that detect, locate, and exploit Russian radio communications, enabling precise targeting of Russian drone operator teams.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cef941579131f01cafedf58b7d330624</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\3.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777932678</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Рации">
  <data key="d0">Рации</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Рации (radios) are traditional military communication devices used by Russian forces, which are vulnerable to interception, decryption, and geolocation by Ukrainian signals intelligence, leading to targeted drone strikes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cef941579131f01cafedf58b7d330624</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\3.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777932678</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Костя">
  <data key="d0">Костя</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Костя is a Russian military personnel or operator referenced in a dialogue, who is questioned about the source of signal for drone operations. entity Зетники organization Зетники are Russian military commentators or content creators on Z-channels who report on Russian drone operations and communication challenges. entity Россия country Россия is the country whose drone operators rely on Starlink and radio communications, and whose tactical effectiveness has been degraded by Ukrainian electronic warfare. entity Украина country Украина is the country whose armed forces have regained dominance in FPV drone operations through improved communication tactics and signals intelligence. entity мотороллы other мотороллы are Russian military radio devices that are vulnerable to interception by Ukrainian signals intelligence due to outdated firmware and lack of secure encryption. entity канадский рэп other канадский рэп refers to a Canadian-made radio device with outdated firmware that was used by Russian forces and proved ineffective against Ukrainian electronic warfare capabilities. relation Костя Зетники dialogue_reference,contextual_actor Костя is referenced in dialogue by Зетники as an example of a Russian operator questioned about signal sources in drone operations. relation Россия Starlink dependency,communication_reliance Россия’s drone operations depend on Starlink for tactical communication, and its disconnection has severely impaired coordination and effectiveness. relation Украина Радиотехническая разведка ВСУ capability_deployment,organizational_support Украина deploys Радиотехническая разведка ВСУ as a key component of its modern warfare strategy to detect and neutralize Russian communication signals. relation мотороллы Радиотехническая разведка ВСУ vulnerability,targeting мотороллы are vulnerable to detection and targeting by Радиотехническая разведка ВСУ due to insecure and unencrypted radio transmissions. relation канадский рэп мотороллы equipment_subtype,technical_failure канадский рэп is an example of a radio device similar to мотороллы, rendered ineffective due to outdated firmware and lack of encryption against Ukrainian signals intelligence.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-cef941579131f01cafedf58b7d330624</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\3.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777932678</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Russian Armed Forces">
  <data key="d0">Russian Armed Forces</data>
  <data key="d1">military_unit</data>
  <data key="d2">The Russian Armed Forces are the military organization of Russia that uses Discord and Starlink for battlefield coordination, and has faced persistent communication challenges in modern warfare.</data>
