<node id="Chechnya">
  <data key="d0">Chechnya</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Chechnya is a region where the Russian army previously experienced systemic communication failures, as mentioned in the context of historical military challenges. entity Georgia location Georgia is a region where the Russian army previously experienced systemic communication failures, as mentioned in the context of historical military challenges. entity Rusha Today organization Rusha Today is a Russian propaganda media channel that published content in 2025 depicting a Russian signalman’s heroic act under fire, highlighting military communication issues. entity Z-kanal organization Z-kanal refers to Russian military propaganda channels that regularly reported on the lack of reliable drone systems comparable to Ukraine’s "Baba Yga." entity Starlink other Starlink is a satellite internet service provided by SpaceX that Russian military forces used for high-precision drone strikes, real-time video transmission, and battlefield coordination, until its access was cut off. entity Windows other Windows is an operating system used by Russian military personnel and command systems, which would be disabled in a conflict with NATO or the United States, per the input text. entity iOS other iOS is an operating system used on devices that Russian military personnel may rely on for communication, which would be disabled in a conflict with NATO or the United States, per the input text. entity Android other Android is an operating system used on devices that Russian military personnel may rely on for communication, which would be disabled in a conflict with NATO or the United States, per the input text. entity Kuznecik v muku other "Kuznecik v muku" is a Russian colloquial phrase meaning "to grind the grasshopper into flour," used metaphorically in the text to describe the act of engaging targets directly on the battlefield. entity SVO conflict SVO (Special Military Operation) is the Russian government’s term for its ongoing military campaign in Ukraine, referenced in the text as the operational zone where internet access was cut off. relation Rusha Today Russian Armed Forces propaganda,depiction Rusha Today, a Russian propaganda channel, published footage in 2025 depicting a Russian signalman’s actions to highlight battlefield communication challenges faced by the Russian Armed Forces. relation Z-kanal Baba Yga comparison,deficiency Z-kanal, Russian military propaganda channels, repeatedly expressed frustration over the lack of an equivalent to Ukraine’s "Baba Yga" drone system, which Russian forces previously replicated using Starlink. relation Russian Armed Forces Windows dependency,communication The Russian Armed Forces depend on Windows-based devices for command and control, which would be disabled in a conflict with NATO or the United States, as stated in the input text. relation Russian Armed Forces iOS dependency,communication The Russian Armed Forces rely on iOS devices for communication, which would be disabled in a conflict with NATO or the United States, as stated in the input text. relation Russian Armed Forces Android dependency,communication The Russian Armed Forces rely on Android devices for communication, which would be disabled in a conflict with NATO or the United States, as stated in the input text. relation Russian Armed Forces SVO operational zone,context The Russian Armed Forces operate within the SVO (Special Military Operation) zone, where internet access was deliberately cut off, severely impacting their communication and drone operations. relation Kuznecik v muku Russian Armed Forces tactical action,metaphor "Kuznecik v muku" is a metaphor used by Russian military personnel in the text to describe the direct engagement of targets on the battlefield, indicating a lack of structured command flow. relation Starlink SVO enabling infrastructure,area of operation Starlink provided critical communication infrastructure within the SVO zone, enabling precision strikes and real-time drone operations that were lost after access was cut off. relation Chechnya Russian Armed Forces historical conflict,communication failure The Russian Armed Forces experienced persistent communication failures during operations in Chechnya, which the text identifies as an enduring systemic problem. relation Georgia Russian Armed Forces historical conflict,communication failure The Russian Armed Forces experienced persistent communication failures during operations in Georgia, which the text identifies as an enduring systemic problem.</data>
