</node>
<node id="Nuclear Deterrence">
  <data key="d0">Nuclear Deterrence</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Nuclear deterrence is a Russian strategy involving threats of limited nuclear use to freeze conventional conflicts and prevent NATO intervention.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1a126839f1ff6597735159d84aa24a61</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\6.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777932845</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Information Warfare">
  <data key="d0">Information Warfare</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Information warfare is a Russian tactic involving propaganda about persecution of Russian speakers in Estonia and Latvia to fabricate justification for intervention and sway European public opinion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1a126839f1ff6597735159d84aa24a61</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\6.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777932845</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Kinetical Phase">
  <data key="d0">Kinetical Phase</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The kinetic phase is the military escalation stage following information warfare, involving unmarked fighters and proxies disabling infrastructure and seizing administrative centers in the Baltic States.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1a126839f1ff6597735159d84aa24a61</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\6.txt</data>
