  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 4 of NATO">
  <data key="d0">Article 4 of NATO</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 4 of NATO is a treaty provision that can be activated when a member state feels its territorial integrity or security is threatened, which would likely occur in response to Russian aggression against the Baltic States.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1a126839f1ff6597735159d84aa24a61</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\6.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777932845</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Article 5 of NATO">
  <data key="d0">Article 5 of NATO</data>
  <data key="d1">document</data>
  <data key="d2">Article 5 of NATO is a treaty provision requiring collective defense, which can only be activated by consensus among all members, and whose activation is questioned in the context of potential Russian aggression.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1a126839f1ff6597735159d84aa24a61</data>
