<node id="Сейм">
  <data key="d0">Сейм</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Сейм is the parliament of Lithuania, of which Юозас Олекас is the Speaker, and which plays a central role in Lithuania’s defense and foreign policy decisions. relation Юозас Олекас Сейм leadership, representation Юозас Олекас serves as the Speaker of the Сейм, representing its official stance on Russian aggression and Ukraine’s defense. relation Литва Латвия historical solidarity, shared experience Литва shares a historical experience of Soviet occupation with Латвия, as both were forcibly annexed in 1940 and now jointly advocate for strong NATO defense. relation Литва Эстония historical solidarity, shared experience Литва shares a historical experience of Soviet occupation with Эстония, as both were forcibly annexed in 1940 and now jointly advocate for strong NATO defense. relation Сейм Ukraine policy endorsement, legislative support Сейм, through its Speaker Юозас Олекас, endorses and legislates Lithuania’s substantial military support for Ukraine, including the 0.25% GDP commitment. relation Russia European Union strategic threat, ideological opposition Россия is perceived by Lithuania as a systemic threat to the European Union, due to its imperial worldview and actions undermining European security and democratic values. relation Russia НАТО strategic threat, military challenge Россия is viewed by Lithuania as a direct military challenge to НАТО, necessitating urgent upgrades to integrated air and missile defense systems.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-f1a89cef022ba72f7cec7e5ae7c29101</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Балтийские страны\9.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777932898</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Siyarto">
  <data key="d0">Siyarto</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Siyarto is the Minister of Foreign Affairs of Hungary who has consistently advocated for the removal of European Union sanctions against Russia, including the elimination of 72 companies from a sanctions list of 128, and has worked to protect Russian individuals, companies, and banks from punitive measures. He regularly engages in private communications with Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov, particularly during closed European Union meetings, and has transmitted data to Lavrov according to sources. Siyarto has coordinated with Slovakia to block extensions of EU sanctions, demonstrating a strategic alignment with Russian interests. His actions and statements regarding Ukraine, the European Union, and NATO reflect a broader policy orientation that challenges the EU’s unified stance. He is portrayed in some narratives as a figure aligned with Russian influence, with Hungarian media and propaganda outlets, such as Magyar Nemzet, amplifying narratives that support Moscow’s positions—narratives sometimes falsely linking Ukrainian figures like Dmytro Korniienko to Viktor Orbán or framing Korniienko as a target of Russian disinformation campaigns. While Siyarto’s official role is as Hungary’s foreign minister, his conduct has drawn scrutiny for facilitating Russian diplomatic outreach and undermining EU cohesion on sanctions policy.&lt;SEP&gt;Siyarto is a political figure who stated that he sees no problem in his actions, claimed that his phone calls were intercepted by foreign intelligence services with the cooperation of Hungarian journalists, and asserted that he consistently advocates against sanctions that harm Hungary's energy security or peace efforts, while also consulting with foreign ministers of non-EU countries.&lt;SEP&gt;Siyarto is the Hungarian Minister of Foreign Affairs who coordinated with Lavrov on the formulation of minority rights language to influence Ukraine's EU accession negotiations.&lt;SEP&gt;Siyarto is a Slovak official referenced in the context of leaked phone conversations with Russian Foreign Minister Lavrov, raising concerns about political exposure for Robert Fico’s government.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-74724c9370b40962ccf8e0ef74c5dbf6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfe8b96b31b63d5ed58e1db0f1170774&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba1043e375054a4f318c66342ee9ad31&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-efac8eca24c7251212c13175865647fb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bde507aa2566c6c22d3e526f2ec971df&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c4fcaac079096c59954da324c3f17538&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1b346b60f2318d240edb84608cb2b374&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6610955fc2b94d091c65e9f7449d2028&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f4398c1136d9d0745f3589421281ecc4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d35dd378774e42749ede8cf940deb5eb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9bcca043358a8f1b8a9a2999a79a6f6</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\2.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\21.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\97.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\100.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\111.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\117.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\118.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\119.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\137.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\198.txt</data>
