<node id="2026 Hungarian Parliamentary Election">
  <data key="d0">2026 Hungarian Parliamentary Election</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The 2026 Hungarian Parliamentary Election is a political event scheduled for April 12, 2026, where Fidesz and Tisza are the main competing forces, and is considered the most competitive in 16 years.&lt;SEP&gt;The 2026 Hungarian parliamentary election is the electoral event scheduled for Sunday, April 12, 2026, in which Viktor Orbán is seeking re-election as Prime Minister of Hungary, with public endorsement from Donald Trump. relation Donald Trump 2026 Hungarian Parliamentary Election endorsement,political intervention Donald Trump explicitly endorses Viktor Orbán’s re-election in the 2026 Hungarian parliamentary election, urging voters to support him and framing it as a continuation of his prior support in 2022. relation Viktor Orbán 2026 Hungarian Parliamentary Election candidacy,election participation Viktor Orbán is the incumbent Prime Minister of Hungary and a candidate in the 2026 Hungarian parliamentary election, seeking re-election with full public backing from Donald Trump.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-aeeb3e654a660cb7b38dfc9d61222bc9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c3129b97ce4bf590efeb8acc86b772e</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\5.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\148.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936888</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Péter Márki-Zay">
  <data key="d0">Péter Márki-Zay</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Péter Márki-Zay is the leader of the Tisza opposition coalition in Hungary and the primary political opponent of Prime Minister Viktor Orbán in the upcoming 2026 parliamentary elections. As the central figure of Tisza, he leads a broad alliance challenging Orbán’s Fidesz party, which is currently polling behind Tisza in electoral surveys. Márki-Zay positions himself as an alternative for voters prioritizing democratic norms, peace, and European integration, sharply criticizing Orbán’s concentration of power and his alignment with Russia. His advocacy for dialogue with European and Ukrainian leaders has made him a target of state-backed disinformation campaigns in Hungary, where he is routinely portrayed in official media as a Brussels puppet, subservient to the European Union, and lacking genuine national support. These narratives are amplified by Kremlin-linked actors, particularly on Russian-language Telegram channels, which depict him as weak and incompetent in contrast to Orbán. Additionally, Márki-Zay is accused by state propaganda of being a traitor to national interests and having a hidden agenda, despite his role in mobilizing public protests against Orbán’s governance. His campaign emphasizes democratic renewal and opposition to authoritarianism, framing Orbán’s policies as destabilizing and internationally isolated. While some descriptions contain conflicting characterizations—such as labeling Tisza as a “party” versus a “coalition”—these are reconcilable as Tisza is a multi-party coalition, with Márki-Zay as its unifying leader. His public image remains polarized: celebrated by opposition supporters as a democratic standard-bearer and vilified by pro-government narratives as a foreign-aligned figurehead.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-aeeb3e654a660cb7b38dfc9d61222bc9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3960e17c128f750dfd948945c91a00ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-443c22f60ed93ec379e718efa356a140&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a865b7c03998478f1296272dd37b2e83&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e1d17587159dea209c75a0ae5875a4b1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3aab01d8a12e8135d55b3153fc006d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2369463d8ede9e477cfaf832815ef3c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6bcd039eb9ab628a1ffb566a855dd2b</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\5.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\8.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\59.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\80.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\104.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\135.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\142.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936757</data>
