</node>
<node id="Hungarian Government">
  <data key="d0">Hungarian Government</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Hungarian Government is an organization that launched a national petition against financial support for Ukraine and claims that Brussels prioritizes Ukraine over European taxpayers.&lt;SEP&gt;The Hungarian Government prepared the transcript of Orbán’s phone call with the Kremlin and released it publicly.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-1cf1470bc49240f9597eaaea1f12646e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bd0a283b39238236a064e8afb069c87</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\7.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Tisa">
  <data key="d0">Tisa</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Tisa is an opposition political party in Hungary, led by Péter Márki-Zay, which is portrayed by state propaganda as a puppet of foreign forces and is accused of secretly planning to send weapons to Ukraine, despite maintaining a cautious stance on aid to Ukraine.&lt;SEP&gt;Tisa is a Hungarian opposition political party led by Пётр Мадяр. It led in several January polls, surpassing Fidesz by 8 to 10 percentage points.&lt;SEP&gt;Tisa is a political party in Hungary that is financially supported by Ukraine, according to the source text.&lt;SEP&gt;Tisa is a Hungarian opposition political party led by Peter Magyar, which has accused the Hungarian government of foreign interference in elections.&lt;SEP&gt;Tisa is an opposition force in Hungary, falsely accused by government representatives of planning a civil war after the elections.&lt;SEP&gt;Tisa is a candidate or option for which the mayor of Bocha cast a vote, as mentioned in the text.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bae0e37e11b33519772a72128c43c6ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cf472d3981c26e07231b309328f0597b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2025a50f1328b82f061a4942a8dd453&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e4bedfc173098465d955c0364c5de9b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-51df0a094ef10ee7cc34dc0f7c1bf5c0</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\8.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\15.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\22.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\50.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\164.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\170.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777937211</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mukachevo">
  <data key="d0">Mukachevo</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Mukachevo is a city in Ukraine’s Zakarpattia region, home to a significant Hungarian minority, which was struck by a Russian missile in August 2025.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\8.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777933036</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Zakarpattia">
  <data key="d0">Zakarpattia</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Zakarpattia is a region in Ukraine where a concentrated Hungarian minority resides, and which is referenced in the context of Russian missile attacks and Hungarian minority concerns.&lt;SEP&gt;Zakarpattia is a region in Ukraine where a Hungarian espionage network operated, gathering intelligence on military defense, public-political sentiments, and potential civilian reactions to Hungarian military intervention.&lt;SEP&gt;Zakarpattia is a region in Ukraine where a Hungarian memorial was falsely depicted in AI-generated images as desecrated by Ukrainian nationalists with Nazi symbols.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d66247a37e4df218b0d4f4b7d7bea3c4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95251bcfc4d08a0a36c341b9a9e2da54</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\8.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\99.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936514</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Péter Szijjártó">
  <data key="d0">Péter Szijjártó</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Péter Szijjártó is the Hungarian Minister of Foreign Affairs who called in the Ukrainian ambassador, prompting a rhetorical question from Anita Orbán about why the Russian ambassador was not summoned after the missile strike on Mukachevo.&lt;SEP&gt;Péter Szijjártó is the Hungarian Foreign Minister who conveyed documents to Sergey Lavrov concerning Ukraine's EU accession negotiations, specifically sections on national minorities to obstruct Ukraine's candidacy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c69b4fdab693c5bb396f844f3d8a77c</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\8.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\138.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936218</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Tamás Sulyok">
  <data key="d0">Tamás Sulyok</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Tamás Sulyok is the President of Hungary who, in his statement regarding the missile strike on Mukachevo, removed the word "Russian" from the description of the attack.&lt;SEP&gt;Tamás Sulyok is the president of Hungary who met with Peter Magyar and is criticized by him for not deserving to be a guardian of the rule of law.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81e671facba3c370c9128965308146dd</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\8.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\191.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777937668</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Anita Orbán">
  <data key="d0">Anita Orbán</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Anita Orbán is a member of the Tisa party specializing in foreign policy and not related to the Hungarian prime minister; she questioned on Facebook why the Russian ambassador was not summoned after the missile strike on Mukachevo.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\8.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777933036</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="World War III">
  <data key="d0">World War III</data>
  <data key="d1">conflict</data>
  <data key="d2">World War III is a rhetorical construct used by Hungarian state propaganda to suggest that supporting Ukraine or changing the government in Budapest would lead to Hungary’s direct military involvement in a global war.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\8.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777933037</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="2026 Hungarian Parliamentary Elections">
  <data key="d0">2026 Hungarian Parliamentary Elections</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The 2026 Hungarian parliamentary elections are framed by Fidesz as a referendum between Orbán’s "party of peace" and the opposition’s "party of war," used to consolidate political support through fear-based messaging.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\8.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777933037</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Deutsche Welle">
  <data key="d0">Deutsche Welle</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Deutsche Welle is the media outlet that published the article analyzing Orbán’s anti-Ukrainian propaganda in Hungary. entity Кеноверзек person Кеноверзек is the author of the article published by Deutsche Welle, as indicated in the source text. relation Deutsche Welle Кеноверзек publication,authorship Deutsche Welle published an article authored by Кеноверзек, which analyzes Orbán’s use of anti-Ukrainian narratives in Hungarian politics. relation Deutsche Welle Orbán reporting,media coverage Deutsche Welle reports on Orbán’s political strategies, including his use of propaganda to shape public opinion on Ukraine and domestic policy. relation Deutsche Welle Fidesz reporting,media coverage Deutsche Welle reports on Fidesz’s manipulation of the 2026 elections as a referendum on Ukraine policy. relation Кеноверзек Orbán reporting,authorship Кеноверзек, as the author of the article, reports on Orbán’s political tactics and propaganda machinery in Hungary. relation Кеноверзек Fidesz reporting,authorship Кеноверзек, as the author of the article, documents Fidesz’s use of anti-Ukrainian narratives to influence voters ahead of the 2026 elections.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e84aa583f7aa058a2cdc38864b8c765a</data>
