<node id="Croatia">
  <data key="d0">Croatia</data>
  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">Croatia is a country associated with a pipeline referenced in the text, which was previously dismissed but later sought after.&lt;SEP&gt;Croatia is a country prepared to supply Slovakia and Hungary with the necessary volume of petroleum products.&lt;SEP&gt;Croatia is a country whose minister, Ante Šušnjar, responded to the deal and plays a supportive role in the energy agreement involving the Adriatic Pipeline.&lt;SEP&gt;Croatia is referenced as a country with infrastructure projects significantly cheaper than analogous projects in Hungary, highlighting corruption in Hungarian public spending under Orbán.&lt;SEP&gt;Croatia is a country through which Hungary could have received oil as an alternative to Russian supplies, but Viktor Orbán refused to use this route.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-01a82c39b89d6badd9ffe2e8f2cc363a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3889b30c247676595bbcc845df96d9ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69d93e1cd4546542fd7a6dd43a3e688d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1561937403235278917e112e7843f5b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3117b3a03ff471f00f67b26aade3e091</data>
