<node id="Financial Times">
  <data key="d0">Financial Times</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Financial Times is a document source that reported on Orbán’s blocking of €90 billion in funding allocated to Ukraine.&lt;SEP&gt;Financial Times is a media organization that reported on the decision of Hungarian opposition parties to withdraw from the April elections to support the Tisza party. relation Financial Times April Elections media coverage,reporting Financial Times reported on the strategic withdrawal of Hungarian opposition parties from the April elections to consolidate support against Fidesz. relation Financial Times Peter Magyar media coverage,reporting Financial Times reported on Peter Magyar’s call for opposition parties to withdraw from the elections to challenge Viktor Orbán’s rule. relation Financial Times Fidesz media coverage,reporting Financial Times reported on Fidesz being trailing behind Tisza in opinion polls ahead of the April elections. relation Financial Times Viktor Orbán media coverage,reporting Financial Times reported on Viktor Orbán’s 16-year rule being challenged by a united opposition front led by Peter Magyar.&lt;SEP&gt;Financial Times is the news outlet reporting on the disinformation campaign orchestrated by Social Design Agency in favor of Viktor Orbán. relation Social Design Agency Hungary influence,electoral interference Social Design Agency conducted a disinformation campaign targeting Hungary’s elections to influence public perception in favor of Viktor Orbán. relation Kremlin Hungary influence,electoral interference The Kremlin, through its linked agency Social Design Agency, influenced Hungary’s electoral process via a coordinated disinformation campaign. relation Social Design Agency Hungarian influencers mediation,indirect coordination Social Design Agency avoided direct contact with Viktor Orbán’s circle and instead used Hungarian influencers to disseminate the disinformation campaign.&lt;SEP&gt;Financial Times is a news organization that reported, citing specific documents, on the structure and operations of the Social Design Agency's disinformation campaign in Hungary.&lt;SEP&gt;Financial Times is a media organization that, alongside V Square, published reports confirming Russian interference in Hungary through a team led by Sergei Kirienko.&lt;SEP&gt;Financial Times is a news organization that reported on internal U.S. and U.K. government tensions regarding security cooperation and restricted access to classified information.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b80d70d8670ebee7e64e3613a75c65de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2886b7cb500c955cf1d8671ed22bd946&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3960e17c128f750dfd948945c91a00ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95251bcfc4d08a0a36c341b9a9e2da54&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3da3b046ca1fff9119eaf735e34f56d4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4528714a664b747f0d79d200f4e5d6ef</data>
