</node>
<node id="Antonio Costa">
  <data key="d0">Antonio Costa</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Antonio Costa is the Chairperson of the European Council who sent a letter to Viktor Orbán reminding Hungary of its commitment to the EU loan agreement for Ukraine.&lt;SEP&gt;Antonio Costa is a political leader who issued a joint statement with Ursula von der Leyen regarding the plan to repair the "Druzhba" pipeline and unlock funds for Ukraine.&lt;SEP&gt;Antonio Costa is the President of the European Council who made an appeal to Ukraine, which is described as insufficient in addressing Ukrainian attacks on Russian energy infrastructure.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-870499425ae897e4d4a7fe9c0c2b515c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0b9d4541f93fbe1abbecc6f52128db7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-204b60f8b5f56bb209e8ca6cc9af48f9</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\26.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\91.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\144.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936815</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sky News">
  <data key="d0">Sky News</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Sky News is a media outlet that reported on the European Council chairperson's call to Viktor Orbán regarding the Ukraine credit agreement. relation European Council Ukraine financial support,diplomatic pressure The European Council, through its chairperson, urged Ukraine to meet conditions for the 90 billion euro credit agreement, as reported by Sky News. relation Sky News Antonio Costa reporting,media coverage Sky News reported on Antonio Costa’s communication with Viktor Orbán regarding the Ukraine credit agreement. relation Sky News Viktor Orbán reporting,media coverage Sky News reported on Viktor Orbán’s stance of blocking the Ukraine credit until Russian oil transit via Druzhba is restored. relation Sky News European Union reporting,media coverage Sky News reported on the European Union’s collective decision regarding the 90 billion euro credit for Ukraine and Hungary’s attempt to block it.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-870499425ae897e4d4a7fe9c0c2b515c</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\26.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777933274</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Kyiv">
  <data key="d0">Kyiv</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Kyiv is a location involved in interfering in Hungary's elections according to the source text.&lt;SEP&gt;Kyiv is the capital of Ukraine, which Viktor Orban claims Hungarian soldiers would be sent to die for.&lt;SEP&gt;Kyiv is the capital of Ukraine, whose future is affected by Hungary’s political alignment under Orbán.&lt;SEP&gt;Kyiv is the capital city of Ukraine and the location to which Robert Fico was invited by Zelensky.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c1d344e42d77e1e71d20f49e3f03482d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c8eeb9a8a3df6bc82ea6fb1da68ab0e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4bd0a283b39238236a064e8afb069c87&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ac57a8e21b0821ebfc4b7007fb6688a3</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\27.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\81.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\201.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777938136</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Twitter/X">
  <data key="d0">Twitter/X</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Twitter/X is the platform where Orbán posted his pre-election statements against Ukraine and the European Union. relation Orbán Twitter/X posting,communication Orbán used Twitter/X to publish his pre-election campaign statements opposing Ukraine and the European Union.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c1d344e42d77e1e71d20f49e3f03482d</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\27.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777933291</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sikorski">
  <data key="d0">Sikorski</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Sikorski is the Minister of Foreign Affairs of Poland who expressed shock at Hungary's lack of solidarity with Ukraine during the Russian invasion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-c1d38d0ea892917e129f8c929d603be9</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\28.txt</data>
