</node>
<node id="Peter Magyar">
  <data key="d0">Peter Magyar</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Peter Magyar is a Hungarian political figure and leader of the opposition party Tisza, who serves as the main challenger to Prime Minister Viktor Orbán. He has called on other opposition groups to withdraw from the April elections to consolidate efforts against Orbán’s ruling coalition, and he was targeted by a strategic electoral maneuver when a spoiler candidate with an identical surname and initials was registered to confuse voters. Magyar has been a vocal critic of Orbán’s policies, accusing him of inviting Russian military intelligence agents to interfere in Hungary’s elections and dismissing allegations of planned violent actions by his movement as fabrications orchestrated by Moscow advisers. On foreign policy, Magyar supports maintaining EU sanctions against Russia, opposes obstructing European aid to Ukraine, and advocates for the gradual diversification of Hungary’s energy supplies away from Russian sources. While acknowledging the necessity of future negotiations with Russia under appropriate conditions, he explicitly states that Russia will not become a friend. He has also demanded that the European Union sever ties with Ukraine until President Zelensky issues an apology, reflecting a complex and sometimes controversial stance on Ukraine policy. Magyar has been the subject of political agitation and is frequently contrasted with the Orbán government’s alleged neglect of domestic issues. Additionally, he has been targeted by AI-generated deepfake content, including a fabricated video depicting him in a car with European Commission President Ursula von der Leyen making false political statements, underscoring the use of disinformation campaigns against him.&lt;SEP&gt;Peter Magyar is the leader of the party "Tisha" who made a statement during a press conference about the actions of the Hungarian Minister of Foreign Affairs.&lt;SEP&gt;Peter Magyar is a politician who is the future prime minister of Hungary and has promised to suspend state media broadcasts. He is the leader of the strongest opposition party and appeared on state media for the first time in one and a half years.&lt;SEP&gt;Peter Magyar is a person who attended an interview on the state Hungarian television channel M1 and announced the dissolution of the channel during the broadcast. entity M1 organization M1 is a state Hungarian television channel that was the subject of an interview with Peter Magyar and was later announced to be dissolved by him. relation Peter Magyar M1 interview,dissolution Peter Magyar attended an interview on M1 and subsequently announced the dissolution of the channel during the broadcast.&lt;SEP&gt;Peter Magyar is the future prime minister of Hungary who accused Viktor Orbán of secretly aiding Robert Fico by directing illegal migrants to Slovakia.&lt;SEP&gt;Peter Magyar is an individual who disclosed information about oligarchs linked to Orbán transferring funds abroad and called for legal action against them.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2886b7cb500c955cf1d8671ed22bd946&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-713408326a31f030b9c00f6efef043ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2025a50f1328b82f061a4942a8dd453&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d3ef991a8152469dff039e1e39a042bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3311af1794addd390d80bf21ccd47d8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95251bcfc4d08a0a36c341b9a9e2da54&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e4bedfc173098465d955c0364c5de9b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3117b3a03ff471f00f67b26aade3e091&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b58528cbdfa8a329180c462cc03756dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81e671facba3c370c9128965308146dd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bde106bd95ba19880a7e7ad13fdc019d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cab9a94ea286a7616cc63009e8c3d5ba&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ad59dda33fb37c7a475f7200ea184cf8</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\30.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\38.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\50.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\65.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\71.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\164.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\182.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\186.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\191.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\192.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\195.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\200.txt</data>
