<node id="Brody Pumping Station">
  <data key="d0">Brody Pumping Station</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Brody Pumping Station is a critical oil infrastructure facility in Ukraine that was attacked by Shahed drones on January 27, resulting in a fire, equipment damage, and the emptying of its main storage tank.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-141360bcc1e8268affe7476ca1b210ea</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\33.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777933482</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Shahed">
  <data key="d0">Shahed</data>
  <data key="d1">military_unit</data>
  <data key="d2">Shahed refers to drones used in an attack on the main storage tank of the Brody Pumping Station.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-141360bcc1e8268affe7476ca1b210ea</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\33.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777933482</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Naftogaz Ukraine">
  <data key="d0">Naftogaz Ukraine</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Naftogaz Ukraine is the Ukrainian state energy company whose main storage tank at Brody was damaged in a Russian strike; its head, Serhiy Kortsyk, confirmed the fire lasted 10 days and described emergency measures taken.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-141360bcc1e8268affe7476ca1b210ea</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\33.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777933482</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Serhiy Kortsyk">
  <data key="d0">Serhiy Kortsyk</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Serhiy Kortsyk is the head of Naftogaz Ukraine who stated that the fire at the Brody Pumping Station lasted 10 days and that emergency oil drainage prevented a larger ecological disaster.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-141360bcc1e8268affe7476ca1b210ea</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\33.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777933482</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Tsargrad TV">
  <data key="d0">Tsargrad TV</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Tsargrad TV is a Kremlin-aligned propaganda media outlet that reported on the fire at the oil depot near Lviv, confirming public knowledge of the incident.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-141360bcc1e8268affe7476ca1b210ea</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\33.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777933482</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Orban">
  <data key="d0">Orban</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Orban is the leader of Hungary who supported a fact-finding mission to Ukraine and denied technical grounds for halting fuel transit despite evidence of Russian strikes.&lt;SEP&gt;Orban is a person who stated that Hungary will suspend the transit of important shipments for Ukraine until the "Druzhba" pipeline is activated.&lt;SEP&gt;Orban is the political leader of Hungary, accused in the text of being bribed by Russia and diverting attention from domestic problems.&lt;SEP&gt;Orban is a political figure who is referenced as using aggressive tactics to mobilize his electorate and is concerned about threats to his family, including his granddaughter Alice.&lt;SEP&gt;Orban is referenced in the context of propaganda that characterizes an influential figure in Zelensky's information space.&lt;SEP&gt;Orban is the Hungarian Prime Minister whose decisive electoral defeat served as a catalyst for Robert Fico’s urgent electoral reforms in Slovakia.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-141360bcc1e8268affe7476ca1b210ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-59d39825ceed8bfe99406c6b226d590f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d3ef991a8152469dff039e1e39a042bd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1919c686ee111f79d9c349e2823ae089&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ff2113969803295df1d948da4243c594&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-09de750ab096b64385f95a95c7d0e5ad</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\33.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\39.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\65.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\67.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\117.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\190.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777937640</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="NASA FIRMS">
  <data key="d0">NASA FIRMS</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">NASA FIRMS is a system that detected thermal signatures of the fire at the Brody Pumping Station on January 28.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-141360bcc1e8268affe7476ca1b210ea</data>
