</node>
<node id="Volodymyr Zelensky">
  <data key="d0">Volodymyr Zelensky</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Volodymyr Zelensky is a political figure who reported on Croatia's willingness to supply petroleum products and commented on Viktor Orbán's reluctance to purchase them.&lt;SEP&gt;Volodymyr Zelensky is the President of Ukraine, mentioned by Peter Magyar as a potential source of eastern threat alongside Vladimir Putin.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3889b30c247676595bbcc845df96d9ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2025a50f1328b82f061a4942a8dd453</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\35.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\50.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777933688</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Croatian Prime Minister">
  <data key="d0">Croatian Prime Minister</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">The Croatian Prime Minister is a person who demonstrated to Volodymyr Zelensky that Croatia can supply the annual petroleum product volume needed by Slovakia and Hungary and expressed readiness to do so. relation Croatian Prime Minister Croatia representation,leadership The Croatian Prime Minister represents Croatia and acts on its behalf in offering petroleum product supplies to Slovakia and Hungary. relation Croatian Prime Minister Volodymyr Zelensky information sharing,diplomatic interaction The Croatian Prime Minister showed the petroleum supply capacity to Volodymyr Zelensky, providing him with direct information about Croatia’s capability.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-3889b30c247676595bbcc845df96d9ee</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\35.txt</data>
