</node>
<node id="Oschadbank">
  <data key="d0">Oschadbank</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Oschadbank is a bank whose employees, armored vehicles, and valuables were seized in Hungary during a regular international currency and bullion transport between Raiffeisen Bank Austria and Oschadbank Ukraine.&lt;SEP&gt;Oschadbank is a Ukrainian financial institution whose cash transport personnel were allegedly abducted, with money and gold bars involved. relation Orbán Oschadbank accusation,propaganda_reference Orbán's campaign banner referenced Oschadbank's gold bars and money as evidence of misappropriation, implying a connection to Ukrainian funds.&lt;SEP&gt;Oschadbank is the Ukrainian state bank whose cash and gold convoy was seized by Hungarian authorities on the Hungary-Ukraine border, with detainees subjected to harsh treatment and property withheld.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-04a007153cdf32c13e7e322795fc37d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d6a8f4f06a47d67e1f0a25d123d913f2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-278b7eddb3c0a5b83b47a5f27d368f14</data>
