<node id="VSquare">
  <data key="d0">VSquare</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Vsquare is an international investigative center in Eastern Europe that reported on the Russian operation in Budapest.&lt;SEP&gt;VSquare is an investigative journalism project that, alongside European security services, uncovered Russian interference in Hungarian parliamentary elections.&lt;SEP&gt;VSquare is a Hungarian media outlet that previously investigated and reported on the presence of Russian military intelligence operatives in Hungary.&lt;SEP&gt;VSquare is a Polish-Hungarian investigative group that reported on the arrival of Russian military intelligence operatives in Hungary, a claim corroborated by European security officials.&lt;SEP&gt;VSquare is a media organization that co-published an investigative report containing the transcript of the conversation between Sergey Lavrov and Péter Szijjártó.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-583ccb318ed3bd5eb71b569940315d4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4c69b4fdab693c5bb396f844f3d8a77c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-325a7fb30b39d268db124a71f1e8acc7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1284d93bbeeeb191a35ec243b4ce4b07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec746b6d0ff03701a4a50f1703d6bbdd</data>
