</node>
<node id="Index">
  <data key="d0">Index</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Index is a Hungarian news portal that reported on the deportation of Ukrainian cash-in-transit officers and the investigation by Hungarian authorities. relation Index Seven Ukrainian Cash-in-Transit Officers reporting,media_coverage Index reported on the deportation of the seven Ukrainian cash-in-transit officers and the circumstances surrounding their detention. relation Index National Tax and Customs Administration reporting,source_information Index reported on the findings and actions of the National Tax and Customs Administration regarding the detention and identification of the individuals. relation Index Government Information Center reporting,source_information Index reported on the statement issued by the Government Information Center concerning the military backgrounds of the deported individuals.&lt;SEP&gt;Index is a source reporting on Hungary's adoption of a resolution regarding Ukraine and the European Union. relation Hungary European Union membership opposition, conflict involvement One of the resolution's points opposes Ukraine's membership in the European Union, arguing it would involve the European Union in war.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-350a5144d8e2787035e85988d9818a16&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1c328a2676af5e886de2f0a15977b2d1</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\42.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\58.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777933793</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="GRU">
  <data key="d0">GRU</data>
  <data key="d1">military_unit</data>
  <data key="d2">GRU is the Russian military intelligence agency whose operatives are alleged to have arrived in Budapest weeks prior to the elections with the intent to influence the outcome.&lt;SEP&gt;GRU is the Russian military intelligence agency whose officers are allegedly operating under diplomatic cover in the Russian embassy in Budapest to conduct information operations similar to those in Chișinău.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b2025a50f1328b82f061a4942a8dd453&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3da3b046ca1fff9119eaf735e34f56d4</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\50.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936516</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Moldova">
  <data key="d0">Moldova</data>
  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">Moldova is the country where Russian military intelligence operatives previously engaged in similar election interference activities, according to the source text.&lt;SEP&gt;Moldova is a post-Soviet country where spoiler technology has been employed, associated with Kremlin-linked political strategists. relation Kremlin Moldova influence, technology transfer Kremlin-linked political technologists applied the spoiler technique in Moldova’s electoral environment.&lt;SEP&gt;Moldova is a country where Andrei Kirienko’s operation failed, prompting a more cautious approach in subsequent activities.&lt;SEP&gt;Moldova is a country where Sergei Kirienko previously directed Russian influence operations during elections, attempting to prevent the re-election of Maia Sandu.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b2025a50f1328b82f061a4942a8dd453&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3311af1794addd390d80bf21ccd47d8f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fa6adba441e776b293e92361b9880d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95251bcfc4d08a0a36c341b9a9e2da54</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\50.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\71.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936506</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Janos Kadar">
  <data key="d0">Janos Kadar</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Janos Kadar is a former Hungarian leader, referenced as the last prior to Viktor Orbán to have invited Russians into Hungary.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b2025a50f1328b82f061a4942a8dd453</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\50.txt</data>
