<node id="János Lázár">
  <data key="d0">János Lázár</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">János Lázár is the Minister of Construction and Transport of Hungary who acknowledged that the seizure of Ukrainian cashiers and theft of money were Hungary's response to Ukraine's blockade of the Druzhba pipeline, and warned of future similar operations. entity Hungary country Hungary is a country whose government, through its Minister János Lázár, admitted to seizing Ukrainian funds and threatening future similar actions in response to Ukraine's blockade of the Druzhba pipeline. entity Ukraine country Ukraine is a country whose operation of the Druzhba pipeline was blocked, leading to Hungary's seizure of Ukrainian cashiers and funds, and who is described as being under financial pressure due to these actions. entity Druzhba location Druzhba is a pipeline whose operation was blocked by Ukraine, prompting Hungary to seize Ukrainian funds and threaten further actions until the pipeline is reopened. relation János Lázár Hungary official role, representation János Lázár, as the Minister of Construction and Transport of Hungary, made statements on behalf of the Hungarian government regarding the seizure of Ukrainian funds and the Druzhba pipeline dispute. relation Hungary Ukraine financial retaliation, conflict Hungary seized Ukrainian funds and threatened future similar operations as a response to Ukraine's blockade of the Druzhba pipeline. relation Hungary Druzhba dependency, strategic interest Hungary linked its financial actions to the reopening of the Druzhba pipeline, indicating its dependence on the pipeline for future financial transfers from Ukraine. relation Ukraine Druzhba blockade, operational control Ukraine blocked the operation of the Druzhba pipeline, which triggered Hungary's financial retaliation and statements by its minister.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-21313de66f58c55ed37fed59c551bfe8</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\57.txt</data>
