</node>
<node id="1848 Hungarian Revolution">
  <data key="d0">1848 Hungarian Revolution</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The 1848 Hungarian Revolution is a historical event commemorated annually in Hungary, during which supporters of Viktor Orbán gathered near the parliament building.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-443c22f60ed93ec379e718efa356a140</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\80.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777933929</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Viktor Orban">
  <data key="d0">Viktor Orban</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Viktor Orban is a prime minister who opposed the Soviet Union in his youth and currently opposes Ukrainians, stating that reelecting him is necessary to prevent Hungarian sons from dying for Kyiv.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orban is a prime minister whose speech was watched by 9–10 thousand people on Facebook and 4 thousand on YouTube.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orban is a politician who began his career in 1989 as a liberal dissident, later shifted his party's ideology to national-conservative, returned as prime minister in 2010, established an illiberal state in Hungary, aligned politically and economically with Vladimir Putin, sabotaged European Union support for Kyiv, and manipulated historical grievances to mobilize his electorate.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orban is a politician whose minister proposed sending European Union documents to Sergey Lavrov through the Hungarian embassy in Moscow.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orban is a political leader of Hungary who has maintained energy policies favoring Russian oil, controlled key financial entities, and used state-aligned media to justify his actions as protecting national interests.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2c8eeb9a8a3df6bc82ea6fb1da68ab0e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2c604c4b50688beffa97c1aa0f1b779&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-30533205f101cc1df47f96e15592f2b3&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9360bf859acb934b8ebad024d1c18290&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a5794dba07f2f01a805d966aa0ee2115</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\81.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\88.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\110.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\136.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1778010500</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
  <data key="d7">Viktor Orban</data>
</node>
<node id="Soviet Union">
  <data key="d0">Soviet Union</data>
  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">The Soviet Union is a former state that Viktor Orban rejected in his youth.&lt;SEP&gt;The Soviet Union is the historical entity against which the slogan "Russians home" was originally directed during the 1956 Hungarian Uprising.&lt;SEP&gt;The Soviet Union is a former state whose intelligence jargon included active measures, which were operational actions aimed at achieving specific political effects in the internal politics of other states.&lt;SEP&gt;The Soviet Union is referenced as the historical actor that brutally suppressed the Hungarian Uprising in 1956 by deploying tanks into Hungary.&lt;SEP&gt;The Soviet Union is the historical entity whose military intervention in Budapest in 1956 is referenced as a precedent for Russian coercive influence in Hungary.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2c8eeb9a8a3df6bc82ea6fb1da68ab0e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-81536517f133c3a5924be660cac3eb05&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fa6adba441e776b293e92361b9880d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5ab60c301522fe44f5b6ce532a3c05b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-35ef5418fbb73e10428a076cc8117782</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\81.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\126.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\151.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\160.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777937007</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Vladimir Zelensky">
  <data key="d0">Vladimir Zelensky</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Vladimir Zelensky is the president of Ukraine, whom Viktor Orban describes as a puppet president.&lt;SEP&gt;Vladimir Zelensky is the President of Ukraine, falsely accused by Hungarian state media of planning armed unrest in Hungary.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-2c8eeb9a8a3df6bc82ea6fb1da68ab0e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e4bedfc173098465d955c0364c5de9b</data>
