</node>
<node id="Gamechanger">
  <data key="d0">Gamechanger</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Gamechanger is a codenamed Russian intelligence strategy to simulate an assassination attempt on Viktor Orbán in order to shift public focus from economic issues to themes of security and stability.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-583ccb318ed3bd5eb71b569940315d4f</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\95.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777934140</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Russian Foreign Intelligence Service">
  <data key="d0">Russian Foreign Intelligence Service</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Russian Foreign Intelligence Service (SVR) is the intelligence organization that drafted the internal report detailing the "Gamechanger" strategy to influence the Hungarian elections by simulating an assassination attempt on Viktor Orbán.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-583ccb318ed3bd5eb71b569940315d4f</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\95.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777934141</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="SvR RF">
  <data key="d0">SvR RF</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">SvR RF is the Russian foreign intelligence service that proposed Operation "GameChanger" to stage an assassination attempt on Viktor Orbán and is involved in discrediting Hungarian opposition figures through disinformation campaigns.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-325a7fb30b39d268db124a71f1e8acc7</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\96.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777934202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Operation &quot;GameChanger&quot;">
  <data key="d0">Operation "GameChanger"</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">Operation "GameChanger" is a proposed Russian intelligence operation designed to stage an assassination attempt on Viktor Orbán to shift public perception of his campaign toward emotional themes of national security and political protection.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-325a7fb30b39d268db124a71f1e8acc7</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\96.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777934202</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="The Washington Post">
  <data key="d0">The Washington Post</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Washington Post is a Western media outlet that reported on internal SvR RF documents provided by European intelligence agencies regarding Russian operations targeting Viktor Orbán.&lt;SEP&gt;The Washington Post is a news publication that confirmed allegations that Hungarian Foreign Minister Sándor Pintér transmitted confidential information to the Kremlin.&lt;SEP&gt;The Washington Post is a news organization that reported on the Hungarian government's offer of assistance to Iran, citing transcripts of government conversations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-325a7fb30b39d268db124a71f1e8acc7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a55a1b2f7d86f155201f7562a7195495&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6f7b78146485b6ecfc5184d01e665fc8</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\96.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\101.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\143.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936787</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Maria Gurozo">
  <data key="d0">Maria Gurozo</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Maria Gurozo is a member of the Hungarian opposition party "Tisza" who was targeted by Russian disinformation campaigns involving fake AI-generated videos.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-325a7fb30b39d268db124a71f1e8acc7</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\96.txt</data>
