  <data key="d5">1777937744</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Sabolc Panyi">
  <data key="d0">Sabolc Panyi</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Sabolc Panyi is a Hungarian investigative journalist who alleged that Hungarian government and private aircraft transported cash and valuables from Russia. relation Sabolc Panyi Hungary allegation,reporting Sabolc Panyi alleged that Hungarian government and private aircraft transported cash and valuables from Russia. relation Hungary Russia transportation,financial flow Hungarian government and private aircraft are alleged to have transported cash and valuables from Russia. relation European Union Russia intelligence reporting National security services of the European Union began receiving data about the transportation of cash and valuables from Russia as early as 2016–2017. relation NATO Russia intelligence reporting National security services of NATO began receiving data about the transportation of cash and valuables from Russia as early as 2016–2017.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e1730c3250b026b4761918dd560d02f0</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\102.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777934351</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="SaS">
  <data key="d0">SaS</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">SaS (Freedom and Solidarity) is an opposition liberal political party in Slovakia led by Bronislav Gerulský, which filed a formal complaint against Robert Fico with the General Prosecutor's Office.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0d2e8519cd0bab60a3e52b70a90d3f0b</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\103.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777934396</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bronislav Gerulský">
  <data key="d0">Bronislav Gerulský</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Bronislav Gerulský is the leader of the opposition liberal party SaS in Slovakia and filed a complaint against Robert Fico, gathering 13,000 signatures.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0d2e8519cd0bab60a3e52b70a90d3f0b</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\103.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777934396</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Druzhba Pipeline">
  <data key="d0">Druzhba Pipeline</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">The Druzhba Pipeline is a critical energy infrastructure targeted by a Russian attack, triggering the cessation of electricity supplies to Ukraine and subsequent political consequences in Slovakia.&lt;SEP&gt;The Druzhba Pipeline is a critical oil infrastructure blocked by Ukraine, which directly influenced Slovakia’s decision to oppose the 20th package of EU sanctions against Russia. relation Robert Fico European Union policy opposition,diplomatic stance Robert Fico, as Prime Minister of Slovakia, publicly stated Slovakia’s refusal to support the European Union’s 20th package of sanctions against Russia. relation Slovakia Ukraine diplomatic tension,infrastructure dispute Slovakia opposes EU sanctions against Russia due to Ukraine’s blockade of the Druzhba Pipeline, indicating diplomatic tension between Slovakia and Ukraine.&lt;SEP&gt;Druzhba Pipeline is a major oil pipeline that transports Russian oil to Hungary, which was damaged by a Russian strike near Brody in Lviv Oblast, leading to supply disruption and political blame directed at Ukraine.&lt;SEP&gt;The Druzhba Pipeline is a major oil pipeline connecting Russia to Central Europe, whose resumption of operations is cited as a possible justification for Robert Fico’s policy shifts.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-0d2e8519cd0bab60a3e52b70a90d3f0b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7fe37316c34f12bcbc2eaa45277e7b90&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-278b7eddb3c0a5b83b47a5f27d368f14&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9bcca043358a8f1b8a9a2999a79a6f6</data>
