<node id="Fides">
  <data key="d0">Fides</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Fides is a Hungarian political party originally founded with a liberal ideology, which Viktor Orban transformed into a national-conservative party in 1994 to increase his political power.&lt;SEP&gt;Fides is the Hungarian political party led by Orbán, whose electoral support is reported to be declining, prompting Russian intelligence to propose disruptive operations to bolster its position.&lt;SEP&gt;Fides is a political organization in Hungary that has been in power for 16 years and is associated with Viktor Orbán; it is accused of using electoral tactics such as voter intimidation and financial manipulation to secure victories.&lt;SEP&gt;Fides is a political party in Hungary; the mayor of Bocha is from this party. relation Mihai Shoke-Tot Fides political affiliation Mihai Shoke-Tot is a member of the Fides party, as stated in the text that he is from the party.&lt;SEP&gt;Fides is a political party whose members distribute bags to voters at some polling stations, according to the source text. entity Torbán person Torbán is the leader of the political party Fides, as implied by the phrase "партии Торбана «Фидес»". relation Fides Torbán leadership,political affiliation Fides is the political party led by Torbán, as indicated by the phrase "партии Торбана «Фидес»".</data>
