</node>
<node id="Mádár">
  <data key="d0">Mádár</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Mádár is a Hungarian opposition figure with stable popularity, public support for change after 16 years of Orbán rule, and a favorable context due to recent scandals.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8fa6adba441e776b293e92361b9880d1</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936506</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Warsaw Pact">
  <data key="d0">Warsaw Pact</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Warsaw Pact is a former military alliance of Eastern Bloc countries, whose leaders were historically treated by Soviet authorities as local administrators-similar to how Viktor Orbán is now viewed by the Kremlin.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8fa6adba441e776b293e92361b9880d1</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936506</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mátyás">
  <data key="d0">Mátyás</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Mátyás is a Hungarian opposition figure referenced in the text as a potential challenger to Viktor Orbán, though the text appears to contain a typographical error where "Mádár" was intended. entity Mádár person Mádár is a Hungarian opposition figure with stable popularity, public support for change after 16 years of Orbán rule, and a favorable context due to recent scandals. relation Mátyás Mádár typographical error, name inconsistency The text mentions "Матьяр" (transliterated as "Mátyás") but contextually refers to "Mádár" - indicating a likely transliteration or typographical error in the source text, requiring clarification. relation Hungary Russia active measure target, geopolitical vulnerability Hungary is targeted by Russian intelligence through active measures, treated as a vulnerable geopolitical space comparable to Cold War regions, despite being a NATO member. relation Kremlin SVR command hierarchy, operational oversight The Kremlin exercises command over the SVR by reviewing and rejecting its operational proposals, demonstrating a top-down structure in Russian foreign influence operations. relation Viktor Orbán Hungary electoral system manipulation, institutional entrenchment Viktor Orbán has engineered Hungary’s electoral system through gerrymandered districts and state media control to ensure disproportionate parliamentary power, entrenching Fidesz rule despite popular opposition. relation Viktor Orbán Putin personal diplomacy, metaphorical self-definition Viktor Orbán refers to himself as a mouse to Putin’s lion in a phone conversation, accurately reflecting his subordinate, instrumental role in the Kremlin’s hierarchy rather than a position of equal partnership. relation Fidesz Hungary state capture, systemic control Fidesz has captured Hungary’s state institutions-including courts, media, central bank, and intelligence agencies-through loyalist appointments, creating a system where democratic norms are formally preserved but functionally hollowed out. relation United States Hungary diplomatic signaling, electoral interference The United States, through a visit by its vice president five days before Hungary’s election, engaged in overt diplomatic signaling intended to influence conservative Hungarian voters in favor of Viktor Orbán. relation Russia Hungary historical parallel, Cold War continuity Russia’s treatment of Hungary as an operational field mirrors its Cold War tactics in Angola and Nicaragua, indicating a continuity in strategy despite changes in geopolitical context. relation Andrei Kirienko Russia operational agent, intelligence operative Andrei Kirienko is a Russian official acting as an operational agent for Russian intelligence, having previously attempted influence operations in Moldova and likely adapting tactics for future use in Hungary.&lt;SEP&gt;Mátyás is the future prime minister of Hungary who stated that no country should be required to give up its territory.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-8fa6adba441e776b293e92361b9880d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-755f0f8d169d5ac73bd77cf98e7bfe35</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\187.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777937453</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Mádiár">
  <data key="d0">Mádiár</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Mádiár is a former insider within Hungary’s Fidesz-led political system, a lawyer and international expert who previously held high-ranking positions in state institutions, including the State Agency for Student Loans and the board of a major state bank. He is the former husband of Judit Varga and publicly exposed corruption within Orbán’s regime, releasing private recordings and accusing the government of embezzlement.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936506</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Judit Varga">
  <data key="d0">Judit Varga</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Judit Varga is the former Minister of Justice of Hungary and the ex-wife of Mádiár. She is described as a close associate of Viktor Orbán and is implicated in discussions about covering up corruption, as revealed in recordings made before her divorce from Mádiár.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936506</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Katalin Novák">
  <data key="d0">Katalin Novák</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Katalin Novák is the former President of Hungary who resigned amid a scandal involving the presidential pardon of a man who covered up pedophilia in a children’s home.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936506</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Antal Rogán">
  <data key="d0">Antal Rogán</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Antal Rogán is a close associate of Viktor Orbán, mentioned in the context of overseeing efforts to suppress evidence in a corruption case, as discussed by Judit Varga in private recordings.&lt;SEP&gt;Antal Rogán is a figure associated with a circle of oligarchs linked to Orbán, whose financial activities are under suspicion for money laundering and who is connected to the media company Lounge Event Kft.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ad59dda33fb37c7a475f7200ea184cf8</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\200.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777938084</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Dzsózsef Orbán">
  <data key="d0">Dzsózsef Orbán</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Dzsózsef Orbán is the 85-year-old father of Viktor Orbán, officially listed as the owner of a large construction site in Hótvágypuszta, Hungary, which is suspected of being a front for Viktor Orbán’s hidden assets.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936506</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Delamit Kft.">
  <data key="d0">Delamit Kft.</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Delamit Kft. is a company owned by Dzsózsef Orbán, Viktor Orbán’s father, which is claimed to generate hundreds of million forints in revenue and is suspected of financing the hidden construction project linked to Viktor Orbán.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936507</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hótvágypuszta">
  <data key="d0">Hótvágypuszta</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Hótvágypuszta is a village in Hungary, near Budapest, where a large, hidden construction project is underway, officially owned by Viktor Orbán’s father but suspected of being a front for his illicit assets.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936507</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Gáncs">
  <data key="d0">Gáncs</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Gáncs is a location in Hungary, associated with Dzsózsef Orbán’s stone quarry business, which is cited as a source of revenue for the family’s financial activities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936507</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Leningrad">
  <data key="d0">Leningrad</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Leningrad is mentioned as the alleged location where Viktor Orbán’s propaganda apparatus supposedly designed Mádiár as a puppet, though this appears to be a misstatement or fictional reference in the text.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936510</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Soros">
  <data key="d0">Soros</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Soros is referenced as a symbolic figure representing Western liberal funding, used by Orbán’s regime to discredit opposition figures, but Mádiár is explicitly noted as not being connected to Soros.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936510</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Lukashenko">
  <data key="d0">Lukashenko</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Alexander Lukashenko is referenced as a comparison figure to Viktor Orbán, highlighting similarities in their public image as modest servants of the nation despite allegations of massive corruption and authoritarian rule.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936510</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Jan Šlais">
  <data key="d0">Jan Šlais</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Jan Šlais is the Hungarian Minister of Construction and Transport who publicly declared that seized Ukrainian funds would not be returned until the Druzhba pipeline is repaired, framing the seizure as a form of leverage.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-278b7eddb3c0a5b83b47a5f27d368f14</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936510</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Brody">
  <data key="d0">Brody</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Brody is a location in Lviv Oblast, Ukraine, where a Russian strike damaged the Druzhba pipeline, leading to the cessation of oil deliveries to Hungary and subsequent political escalation by Orbán.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-278b7eddb3c0a5b83b47a5f27d368f14</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936510</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="RaiFaiZen Bank">
  <data key="d0">RaiFaiZen Bank</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">RaiFaiZen Bank is an Austrian bank that coordinated a legitimate cash transfer with Oschadbank, which was intercepted by Hungarian authorities on the Hungary-Ukraine border.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-278b7eddb3c0a5b83b47a5f27d368f14</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936510</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Ashatbank">
  <data key="d0">Ashatbank</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Ashatbank is the Ukrainian bank that received funds from RaiFaiZen Bank via a pre-approved ground transport route through Hungary, which was seized by Hungarian authorities.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-278b7eddb3c0a5b83b47a5f27d368f14</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="22 February">
  <data key="d0">22 February</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">22 February is the date when Orbán blocked the 20th EU sanctions package against Russia and the €90 billion EU credit line to Ukraine, citing Ukrainian sabotage of the Druzhba pipeline as justification.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-278b7eddb3c0a5b83b47a5f27d368f14</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="5 March">
  <data key="d0">5 March</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">5 March is the date when Hungarian counterterrorism services seized a cash and gold convoy from Oschadbank on the Hungary-Ukraine border, detaining staff and confiscating assets.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-278b7eddb3c0a5b83b47a5f27d368f14</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="27 January">
  <data key="d0">27 January</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">27 January is the date when a Russian strike damaged the Druzhba pipeline near Brody, Ukraine, disrupting oil deliveries to Hungary and prompting Orbán to blame Ukraine.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-278b7eddb3c0a5b83b47a5f27d368f14</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="2026–2027">
  <data key="d0">2026–2027</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">2026–2027 refers to the years for which the €90 billion EU credit line to Ukraine was intended to support war funding and state operations.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-278b7eddb3c0a5b83b47a5f27d368f14</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Lviv Oblast">
  <data key="d0">Lviv Oblast</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Lviv Oblast is a region in Ukraine where the Russian strike damaged the Druzhba pipeline near Brody, leading to disruption of oil supplies to Hungary. entity RaiFaiZen Bank organization RaiFaiZen Bank is an Austrian bank that coordinated a legitimate cash transfer with Oschadbank, which was intercepted by Hungarian authorities on the Hungary-Ukraine border. entity Ashatbank organization Ashatbank is the Ukrainian bank that received funds from RaiFaiZen Bank via a pre-approved ground transport route through Hungary, which was seized by Hungarian authorities. relation Lviv Oblast Druzhba Pipeline location,infrastructure The Druzhba Pipeline runs through Lviv Oblast, where the Russian strike damaged the Ukrainian section of the pipeline near Brody. relation RaiFaiZen Bank Ashatbank financial transfer,cooperation RaiFaiZen Bank and Ashatbank conducted a pre-approved, legitimate cash transfer through Hungary, which was illegally intercepted by Hungarian authorities. relation Hungary RaiFaiZen Bank transit violation,interception Hungary intercepted a cash convoy originating from RaiFaiZen Bank, violating established transit agreements despite prior coordination. relation Hungary Ashatbank asset seizure,unlawful detention Hungary seized funds destined for Ashatbank and detained its personnel, despite the transaction being fully documented and lawful. relation 2026–2027 Ukraine funding period,financial need The €90 billion EU credit line was intended for Ukraine’s war funding and state operations during 2026–2027, making this period critical for its survival. relation European Union 2026–2027 funding commitment,planned duration The European Union committed the €90 billion credit line to Ukraine specifically for the years 2026–2027 to ensure continued state functionality and war financing. relation Ukraine 2026–2027 reliance,funding horizon Ukraine depends on the €90 billion EU funding committed for 2026–2027 to sustain its government and military operations during this critical period. relation Jan Šlais European Union policy defiance,member state violation Jan Šlais publicly endorsed asset seizure as state policy, directly defying European Union principles of rule of law and mutual trust among member states. relation Kremlin Ukraine military attack,infrastructure targeting The Kremlin conducted a military strike targeting the Druzhba pipeline in Ukraine, causing disruption to energy flows and triggering a political crisis in Hungary. relation Oschadbank European Union institutional alignment,legitimacy Oschadbank, as Ukraine’s state bank, operates under EU-recognized financial protocols, making its seizure by Hungary a violation of EU institutional norms. relation 22 February European Union sanctions blockade,policy obstruction On 22 February, Hungary, under Orbán, blocked the European Union’s 20th sanctions package against Russia, obstructing collective EU foreign policy. relation 5 March European Union rule of law violation,member state breach On 5 March, Hungary’s seizure of Ukrainian state funds violated the European Union’s foundational commitment to the rule of law and protection of member state assets. relation Druzhba Pipeline Kremlin target,attack site The Druzhba Pipeline near Brody was the target of a Kremlin military strike, which directly caused the oil supply disruption to Hungary. relation Hungary Kremlin strategic alignment,energy dependency Hungary’s refusal to sanction Russia and insistence on restoring Russian oil flows indicate strategic alignment with Kremlin energy interests. relation Orbán 2026–2027 political leverage,electoral timing Orbán leveraged the 2026–2027 EU funding timeline for Ukraine to amplify fear among Hungarian voters, framing delayed aid as existential threat. relation Oschadbank Hungary transit corridor,agreed protocol Oschadbank’s cash transfers through Hungary followed a long-established, agreed-upon protocol, which Hungary violated by seizing assets and detaining personnel. relation Jan Šlais Hungary policy spokesperson,public justification Jan Šlais acted as the public spokesperson for Hungary’s policy of using asset seizure as a tool of foreign leverage, explicitly justifying it as retaliation. relation European Union Hungary membership crisis,ideological fracture Hungary’s actions have created a deep membership crisis within the European Union, exposing a fracture between EU norms and the policies of an authoritarian-leaning member state.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-278b7eddb3c0a5b83b47a5f27d368f14</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Jared Vance">
  <data key="d0">Jared Vance</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Jared Vance is the U.S. Vice President who visited Budapest five days before Hungary’s elections to support Orbán.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bd0a283b39238236a064e8afb069c87</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936511</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hungarian Election">
  <data key="d0">Hungarian Election</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The Hungarian Election is a national vote occurring on a Sunday, the outcome of which significantly impacts the future of Budapest, Brussels, Kyiv, and Moscow.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4bd0a283b39238236a064e8afb069c87</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hungarian Ministry of Economy">
  <data key="d0">Hungarian Ministry of Economy</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Hungarian Ministry of Economy is the government body that reported Hungary became a net contributor to the EU budget for the first time since 2004, indicating economic decline.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e4089c9c991c6402b317d88ca6848ab9</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="EU Recovery Fund">
  <data key="d0">EU Recovery Fund</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">EU Recovery Fund is a financial instrument of the European Union designed to support member states post-pandemic, from which Hungary lost €9.5 billion due to frozen funds.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e4089c9c991c6402b317d88ca6848ab9</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Cohesion Funds">
  <data key="d0">Cohesion Funds</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Cohesion Funds are EU financial resources intended to reduce regional disparities, of which Hungary lost €8.5 billion due to failure to meet reform conditions.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e4089c9c991c6402b317d88ca6848ab9</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hungarian public procurement system">
  <data key="d0">Hungarian public procurement system</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Hungarian public procurement system is a state mechanism used to redistribute funds to loyal businesses, which Orbán preserved by refusing anti-corruption reforms.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e4089c9c991c6402b317d88ca6848ab9</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hungarian education and healthcare infrastructure">
  <data key="d0">Hungarian education and healthcare infrastructure</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Hungarian education and healthcare infrastructure is the domain that could have benefited from €19 billion in EU funds, but suffered due to reforms not being implemented.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e4089c9c991c6402b317d88ca6848ab9</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CRP">
  <data key="d0">CRP</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">CRP is referred to in the text as one of the most media-aggressive pro-Putin politicians in Europe, likely a misstatement or abbreviation for Peter Szijjártó.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e4089c9c991c6402b317d88ca6848ab9</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936512</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="MO">
  <data key="d0">MO</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">MO is a Hungarian oil company and monopoly on the domestic fuel market that receives Russian oil via the Druzhba pipeline at prices approximately 20% below global market rates, forming the financial backbone of Viktor Orbán’s energy policy.&lt;SEP&gt;MO is Hungary's largest oil company that has seen a 30% increase in operational profit during the war, with a significant portion of its profits distributed as dividends to foundations controlled by Viktor Orban.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a5794dba07f2f01a805d966aa0ee2115&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc1feb8e698e39594612de628b9b30f8</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936513</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Matthias Corvinus Collegium">
  <data key="d0">Matthias Corvinus Collegium</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Matthias Corvinus Collegium is an educational institution affiliated with Viktor Orban and owns over 30% of MO, receiving dividends from its profits.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a5794dba07f2f01a805d966aa0ee2115</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936513</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="CNN">
  <data key="d0">CNN</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">CNN is an international news organization that published an investigation by the Bulgarian Center for the Study of Democracy regarding Hungary’s energy deals and financial flows tied to Russian oil.&lt;SEP&gt;CNN is a media organization that published a study by a Bulgarian democracy research center analyzing the true cost of Hungary’s energy policy.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a5794dba07f2f01a805d966aa0ee2115&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc1feb8e698e39594612de628b9b30f8</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936513</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Bulgarian Center for the Study of Democracy">
  <data key="d0">Bulgarian Center for the Study of Democracy</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">The Bulgarian Center for the Study of Democracy is a research institution that conducted an analysis for CNN on Hungary’s discounted Russian oil imports and their financial implications.&lt;SEP&gt;Bulgarian Center for the Study of Democracy is a research institution that conducted an analysis revealing the financial mechanisms behind Hungary’s fuel pricing and profit diversion.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a5794dba07f2f01a805d966aa0ee2115&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc1feb8e698e39594612de628b9b30f8</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936513</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hatyapust">
  <data key="d0">Hatyapust</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Hatyapust is a private zoo in Hungary associated with Viktor Orban’s power structure, funded by profits from the energy scheme.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-a5794dba07f2f01a805d966aa0ee2115</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936513</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Newgard">
  <data key="d0">Newgard</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Newgard is an organization that identified and reported 34 anonymous TikTok accounts generating AI videos against Peter Magyar, with a combined reach of approximately 10 million views, and alerted TikTok to the operation.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-95251bcfc4d08a0a36c341b9a9e2da54</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936513</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="TikTok">
  <data key="d0">TikTok</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">TikTok is a social media platform that officially confirmed the blocking of 34 hidden influence accounts after being provided with a list by Newgard.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-95251bcfc4d08a0a36c341b9a9e2da54</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936513</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="V Square">
  <data key="d0">V Square</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">V Square is a Hungarian independent media outlet that, in collaboration with Financial Times, exposed Russian political technologists operating in Hungary under Sergei Kirienko’s leadership.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-95251bcfc4d08a0a36c341b9a9e2da54</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936514</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Maia Sandu">
  <data key="d0">Maia Sandu</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Maia Sandu is the President of Moldova who was re-elected despite Russian interference efforts led by Sergei Kirienko during the previous election cycle.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-95251bcfc4d08a0a36c341b9a9e2da54</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936514</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Michael Naki">
  <data key="d0">Michael Naki</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Michael Naki is the speaker in the input text who delivers a commentary on Viktor Orbán’s political strategy, drawing an analogy between Orbán and a mouse in a fable, and urges Hungarian audiences to act before the next election.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-de92df91fd68b8019a5e2c98e87d545e</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
