  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="ML">
  <data key="d0">ML</data>
  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">ML refers to a source of dividends mentioned in the context of Viktor Orbán’s personal benefits, likely an abbreviation for a specific entity or fund tied to his regime’s financial gains. entity Брюссель other Брюссель (Brussels) is referenced as a symbolic representation of the European Union institutions, which Viktor Orbán claims to oppose while simultaneously benefiting from their funding. entity Сиярта other Сиярта is referenced as an entity that directly instructed Lavrov regarding discussions on sanctions, indicating a channel of communication or authority within the Russian government structure. relation Viktor Orbán ML financial benefit, personal gain Viktor Orbán received financial benefits, including dividends from ML, as part of the personal rewards tied to his political alignment with Russian interests. relation Viktor Orbán Брюссель political opposition, rhetorical framing Viktor Orbán framed Brussels as an adversary to justify his authoritarian policies and maintain domestic support, while continuing to accept EU financial support. relation Сиярта Sergey Lavrov directive, internal command Сиярта issued direct instructions to Sergey Lavrov concerning discussions on sanctions, indicating a hierarchical or operational link within Russian political-military communication channels.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-de92df91fd68b8019a5e2c98e87d545e</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936514</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="József Orbán">
  <data key="d0">József Orbán</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">József Orbán is the eighty-five-year-old father of Viktor Orbán, officially listed as the owner of a farming enterprise in Hatvanpusta, and the head of Delamit Kft, a company with a stone quarry in Gánt.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fc1feb8e698e39594612de628b9b30f8</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936514</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Delamit Kft">
  <data key="d0">Delamit Kft</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">Delamit Kft is a company owned by József Orbán, operating a stone quarry in Gánt and reportedly generating hundreds of millions of forints in revenue, used to justify the construction of the Hatvanpusta estate.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fc1feb8e698e39594612de628b9b30f8</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936514</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Hatvanpusta">
  <data key="d0">Hatvanpusta</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Hatvanpusta is a property in Hungary associated with Viktor Orbán’s father, featuring a mansion with extensive luxury amenities including pools, underground tunnels, a palm grove, chapel, solar power station, and a private zoo with zebras, antelopes, and buffaloes.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-fc1feb8e698e39594612de628b9b30f8</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777936514</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Akashhadhazi">
  <data key="d0">Akashhadhazi</data>
  <data key="d1">person</data>
  <data key="d2">Akashhadhazi is an opposition Hungarian MP and licensed pilot who, with a TV crew, flew over Hatvanpusta and documented its luxury features, later organizing protests and tours near the estate.</data>
