<node id="2022 Hungarian Elections">
  <data key="d0">2022 Hungarian Elections</data>
  <data key="d1">event</data>
  <data key="d2">The 2022 Hungarian elections are referenced as a previous electoral event with significantly lower voter turnout rates compared to the current election.&lt;SEP&gt;The 2022 Hungarian Elections were the previous national elections in which Fidesz won 88 of 106 districts and secured 54% of the vote to gain 135 parliamentary seats through a biased electoral system.&lt;SEP&gt;The 2022 Hungarian elections resulted in Fidesz’s dominance across the country, with Budapest being the primary exception, and saw 59% of the population view Orbán as the most reliable candidate to avoid war.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-b6bcd039eb9ab628a1ffb566a855dd2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-867b81690ecba5bc75830acd44c39131&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e4bedfc173098465d955c0364c5de9b</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\142.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\164.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777937112</data>
