  <data key="d1">other</data>
  <data key="d2">Russians is a term used in the protest slogan "Russians go home!" as a symbolic reference to perceived Russian influence in Hungary, evoking historical resentment tied to Soviet intervention. relation Hungary Russians symbolic opposition, anti-influence sentiment Protesters in Hungary used the slogan "Russians go home!" to express symbolic opposition to Russian influence, drawing a direct parallel to Soviet occupation during the 1956 Hungarian Uprising.&lt;SEP&gt;Russians are a group targeted by chants at opposition rallies in Hungary, with demonstrators demanding they go home.</data>
