<node id="KDH">
  <data key="d0">KDH</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">KDH is a Slovak opposition party with support between 5–7%, likely to cooperate with Progressive Slovakia and affected by the proposed increase in the electoral threshold. relation Robert Fico KDH target, suppress Robert Fico’s proposed increase in the electoral threshold from 5% to 7% is intended to exclude KDH and other mid-sized opposition parties from parliament. relation Robert Fico 2026 Municipal Elections avoid, delay Robert Fico proposes extending local council terms from 4 to 5 years to avoid holding municipal elections in 2026 and prevent public demonstration of declining government trust. relation Robert Fico Electoral Code Amendment propose, initiate Robert Fico’s government is preparing and initiating the Electoral Code Amendment to alter Slovakia’s electoral system in favor of his party’s electoral survival. relation Electoral Code Amendment Hlas receive support from The Electoral Code Amendment has received preliminary support from Hlas up to the second reading, indicating a strategic legislative alignment. relation Orban Slovakia influence, catalyst Orban’s electoral defeat in Hungary served as a catalyst for Robert Fico’s urgent electoral reforms in Slovakia, demonstrating vulnerability of populist leaders. relation Robert Fico Electoral Threshold Increase propose, implement Robert Fico proposes increasing the electoral threshold from 5% to 7% to exclude opposition parties with 5–7% support from entering parliament. relation Robert Fico Postal Voting Ban propose, eliminate Robert Fico proposes eliminating postal voting for expatriate voters to remove a source of votes predominantly favoring anti-government parties. entity Postal Voting Ban other The Postal Voting Ban is a proposed measure in Slovakia’s electoral reform to disqualify votes cast by citizens abroad, which historically favored opposition parties. entity Electoral Threshold Increase other The Electoral Threshold Increase is a proposed change in Slovakia’s electoral law to raise the minimum vote percentage required for parliamentary entry from 5% to 7%. entity Electoral Deposit Increase other The Electoral Deposit Increase is a proposed measure to raise the financial deposit required for party participation in elections from €17,000 to approximately €40,500, aimed at deterring small and mid-sized opposition parties. relation Robert Fico Electoral Deposit Increase propose, implement Robert Fico proposes increasing the electoral deposit from €17,000 to approximately €40,500 to hinder participation by small and mid-sized opposition parties. relation Robert Fico Multi-Mandate District Redistricting propose, implement Robert Fico proposes replacing the single multi-member district with multiple multi-member districts to favor large parties like Smer with concentrated regional support. entity Multi-Mandate District Redistricting other Multi-Mandate District Redistricting is a proposed electoral reform in Slovakia to replace the current single nationwide district with multiple regional districts, benefiting parties with strong regional bases like Smer.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-09de750ab096b64385f95a95c7d0e5ad</data>
  <data key="d4">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\190.txt</data>
  <data key="d5">1777937641</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
