  <data key="d2">South Korea is a country to which two North Korean prisoners of war in Ukraine have requested to be transferred, according to a South Korean human rights organization cited by AFP.&lt;SEP&gt;South Korea is the country whose capital, Seoul, is criticized in the text for responding inadequately to North Korea’s escalatory actions, treating border violations as accidental or negotiable rather than requiring urgent military response. relation North Korea South Korea border conflict, military escalation North Korea conducts repeated border crossings and provocative military movements against South Korea, escalating tensions along the Korean Demilitarized Zone. relation Pyongyang South Korea strategic provocation, deterrence failure Pyongyang’s military actions, including deployment of combat-experienced units, are directed toward South Korea, while South Korea’s response is portrayed as insufficient and enabling further escalation.&lt;SEP&gt;South Korea is a country whose coast guard conducted a boarding operation against a Chinese fishing vessel violating territorial waters.&lt;SEP&gt;South Korea’s intelligence agency asserts that North Korea sent approximately 33,000 containers of military equipment to Russia, including over 15 million 152-mm artillery shells and 220 artillery systems. entity Defense Intelligence Agency organization The Defense Intelligence Agency of the United States corroborates information regarding North Korea’s military shipments to Russia, as referenced in the source text. relation South Korea North Korea intelligence assessment, military surveillance South Korea’s intelligence agency reported that North Korea shipped large volumes of military equipment to Russia, including artillery shells and systems. relation Defense Intelligence Agency United States institutional affiliation The Defense Intelligence Agency is the military intelligence arm of the United States Department of Defense and provided corroboration of North Korea’s military shipments to Russia. relation South Korea United States intelligence collaboration South Korea’s intelligence findings regarding North Korea’s military shipments to Russia were corroborated by the United States’ Defense Intelligence Agency.&lt;SEP&gt;South Korea is a country whose population's attitudes toward North Koreans are examined, and which, alongside North Korea, influences the global scene as mentioned in the video title.</data>
