  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">Russian Federation is a country whose delegation held negotiations with North Korea regarding North Korean participation in the war against Ukraine, and which received military personnel and weapons from North Korea. entity Democratic People's Republic of Korea country Democratic People's Republic of Korea is a country that sent military personnel and weapons to support Russian Federation in the war against Ukraine, and whose delegation participated in negotiations with Russian Federation. entity North Korean military personnel military_unit North Korean military personnel are soldiers from the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, with approximately 15,000 deployed to support Russian Federation in the war against Ukraine since October 2024, and up to 5,000 more planned to be sent following negotiations. entity Ministry of Defense of the Russian Federation organization Ministry of Defense of the Russian Federation is an organization represented by its deputy minister in the delegation that held negotiations with Democratic People's Republic of Korea. entity Korean Central News Agency organization Korean Central News Agency is the state-run information agency of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea that reported the negotiations occurred in a friendly atmosphere. entity National Intelligence Service of South Korea organization National Intelligence Service of South Korea is an intelligence agency that reported the outcome of the negotiations, including the planned deployment of North Korean military personnel to Russia. entity Radio Free Europe organization Radio Free Europe is an organization mentioned as a source for the input text, providing context and encouraging subscriptions. relation Russian Federation Democratic People's Republic of Korea negotiation,military cooperation,war alliance The delegation of the Russian Federation held negotiations with the Democratic People's Republic of Korea regarding North Korean military participation in the war against Ukraine, resulting in coordinated military support. relation Democratic People's Republic of Korea North Korean military personnel deployment,military support The Democratic People's Republic of Korea deployed approximately 15,000 North Korean military personnel to support the Russian Federation in the war against Ukraine, with an additional 5,000 planned after negotiations. relation Democratic People's Republic of Korea Russian Federation weapons transfer,military aid The Democratic People's Republic of Korea provided weapons to the Russian Federation to support its military operations against Ukraine. relation Ministry of Defense of the Russian Federation Russian Federation representation,negotiation participation The deputy minister of the Ministry of Defense of the Russian Federation was part of the delegation that conducted negotiations with the Democratic People's Republic of Korea on behalf of the Russian Federation. relation Korean Central News Agency Democratic People's Republic of Korea reporting,official communication The Korean Central News Agency, as the state media of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, reported that the negotiations with the Russian Federation occurred in a friendly atmosphere. relation National Intelligence Service of South Korea Russian Federation intelligence reporting,military assessment The National Intelligence Service of South Korea reported that, following negotiations, up to 5,000 North Korean military personnel would be sent to the Russian Federation for the war against Ukraine.</data>
