<node id="КНДР">
  <data key="d0">КНДР</data>
  <data key="d1">country</data>
  <data key="d2">КНДР (Корейская Народно-Демократическая Республика) is a country that plans to supply pharmaceuticals to Russia, according to the source text.&lt;SEP&gt;КНДР is the country whose military is using the war in Ukraine as a training ground to modernize its armed forces through battlefield experience, rotation of troops, and acquisition of drone warfare capabilities.&lt;SEP&gt;КНДР is a country that supplied between 8 and 11 million ammunition units to Russia through maritime transport over two and a half years, averaging about 350,000 rounds per month.&lt;SEP&gt;КНДР is the abbreviated name for Северная Корея and received advanced military technologies from Russia in exchange for weapons and personnel, contributing to its 2024 GDP growth. relation КНДР Russia military assistance, technology transfer, barter economy КНДР provided weapons and military personnel to Russia, and in return received advanced military technologies and components, with payment primarily in kind rather than cash.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-e5d2b942a2c7c68f8c9998675a0bad2f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ec36c3f34e874fb6a0c44b533c707cfe&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b1c5a44337225374fecdeb2a9881ccb4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f525f78f89f5b96d8fc7535b3303ae6b</data>
