<node id="Gloucestershire">
  <data key="d0">Gloucestershire</data>
  <data key="d1">location</data>
  <data key="d2">Gloucestershire is a county in the United Kingdom where RAF Fairford is located, and it is referenced as the geographic location of a British air base involved in U.S. military access requests. relation United States United Kingdom security policy,diplomatic friction,base access The United States has experienced increased delays in obtaining approval to use British military bases, including RAF Fairford, for operations related to Iran, marking a departure from previously automatic approvals and contributing to bilateral tension. relation United Kingdom United States security policy,diplomatic reassurance British officials assert that security cooperation remains intact and that all U.S. requests are evaluated individually under international agreements, aiming to reassure the U.S. despite operational delays.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-4528714a664b747f0d79d200f4e5d6ef</data>
