<edge source="Cuba" target="United States">
  <data key="d8">4.0</data>
  <data key="d9">The president of Cuba announced the beginning of negotiations with the United States, which triggered further protests.&lt;SEP&gt;The United States has blocked oil shipments to Cuba since January, leading to power outages and prohibiting Cuba from purchasing Russian oil.&lt;SEP&gt;The United States expressed concern that foreign intelligence, military, and terrorist groups are operating with the Cuban government’s approval near U.S. territory.&lt;SEP&gt;United States and Cuba held their first secret talks in 10 years in Havana, marking a resumption of direct diplomatic engagement.</data>
  <data key="d10">diplomatic engagement,energy blockade,foreign influence,negotiation,sanction,secret talks,security concern</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-3d31f0e0677eda8305196001171ef666&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9ebb3ed519c434b35de7bc7a410af22&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-07e1a126d8b8691b4020263f5c90fd4b</data>
