<edge source="United States" target="Russia">
  <data key="d8">5.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Russia assumes the United States is naive in its approach to its military ambitions, and Russian officials expect the U.S. to recognize the necessity of confronting Russian aggression.&lt;SEP&gt;Russia assumes the United States remains naive about its intentions, and Russian officials expect the U.S. to eventually confront the reality of Russia’s military ambitions.&lt;SEP&gt;The role of the United States in a potential conflict between Russia and Europe remains undefined, creating strategic uncertainty for Russian planning.&lt;SEP&gt;The United States is portrayed as an unreliable NATO ally, reducing confidence in collective defense against Russian aggression.&lt;SEP&gt;The United States has begun lifting sanctions on Russian oil, contrasting with the European Union's stance, according to Viktor Orbán.</data>
  <data key="d10">alliance distrust,energy policy,geopolitical confrontation,geopolitical rivalry,military posture,sanctions lift,strategic ambiguity,strategic challenge,strategic miscalculation,unreliable partner</data>
