<edge source="United States" target="Hungary">
  <data key="d8">5.0</data>
  <data key="d9">The United States sent Jey D. Vens to Hungary to express opposition to EU interference and to affirm support for Hungary's national sovereignty and democratic rights.&lt;SEP&gt;Hungarian officials discussed the Adriatic Pipeline with their American counterparts, presenting it as a viable solution during meetings in Washington.&lt;SEP&gt;The United States, through a visit by its vice president five days before Hungary’s election, provided direct political support to Viktor Orbán’s campaign, influencing conservative voter perceptions.&lt;SEP&gt;The United States and Hungary have developed strengthened cooperation and achievements during Donald Trump's administration, attributed to the leadership of Viktor Orbán.&lt;SEP&gt;The United States, through its administration, is willing to invest in Hungary's future prosperity under the continued leadership of Viktor Orbán.</data>
  <data key="d10">cooperation,diplomatic engagement,diplomatic intervention,diplomatic support,economic investment,electoral influence,sovereignty endorsement,strategic negotiation,strategic partnership</data>
