<edge source="Russia" target="Poland">
  <data key="d8">4.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Russian aggression following the conflict in Ukraine is perceived by Germans as a potential threat to NATO member Poland.&lt;SEP&gt;Poland constructed the Eastern Shield fortifications along its border with Russia to deter potential aggression, though the design is criticized as flawed.&lt;SEP&gt;Russia’s plan to sever the Suwałki Corridor directly threatens Poland’s connection to Lithuania and its role in Baltic defense.&lt;SEP&gt;Poland does not depend on Russian oil, which contributes to its lower fuel prices compared to Hungary.</data>
