<edge source="Russia" target="Viktor Orbán">
  <data key="d8">11.0</data>
  <data key="d9">The relationship between Russia and Viktor Orbán is characterized by strategic alignment, mutual political benefit, and deepening ideological and economic ties. Viktor Orbán, Prime Minister of Hungary, has consistently pursued policies favorable to Russian interests, including advocating for the lifting of sanctions on Russian energy and preferring to purchase petroleum at Russian prices rather than higher European market rates, thereby securing financial advantages aligned with Moscow’s energy strategy. Orbán’s political rhetoric and governance model—marked by media control, suppression of dissent, and centralization of power—are frequently compared to those of Vladimir Putin’s Russia, reflecting a shared authoritarian orientation. He has positioned himself as an alternative to Western institutions, cultivating a friendly personal and political relationship with Putin, whom he has publicly described as a “lion” to his own “mouse,” acknowledging his subordinate yet instrumental role within the Kremlin’s hierarchy. Russia, in turn, has actively sought to ensure Orbán’s electoral success through coordinated political and intelligence operations, including disinformation campaigns that portray the Hungarian opposition as Western agents and the use of nuclear threats to destabilize domestic opposition. Orbán is also accused of inviting representatives of Russian military intelligence into Hungary to influence electoral outcomes, further implicating his administration in direct collaboration with Russian state actors. Together, these actions underscore a symbiotic relationship in which Orbán gains political stability and economic relief through Russian support, while Russia gains a reliable ally within the European Union who undermines unified Western policy toward Moscow.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orbán acted as a Kremlin puppet by receiving direct orders from the Kremlin and refusing to diversify energy supplies, insisting on importing Russian oil despite alternatives.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orbán's government maintained close energy ties with Russia, a relationship acknowledged by Russian newspapers as beneficial to Hungary.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orbán maintained a political alliance with Russia, symbolized by his self-description as "the mouse" to Putin, which is now used as a cautionary reference for Robert Fico.</data>
  <data key="d10">alliance,disinformation,electoral influence,energy cooperation,energy dependence,energy dependency,energy procurement,foreign interference,foreign support,ideological_similarity,invitation,metaphorical alignment,policy alignment,political alignment,political alliance,political_alignment,price preference,self-perception,strategic alignment,subordination,support,symbolic subservience</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-3889b30c247676595bbcc845df96d9ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1284d93bbeeeb191a35ec243b4ce4b07&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b2025a50f1328b82f061a4942a8dd453&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d9aedd80ca30611f4314d3afe2ee2ad0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fa6adba441e776b293e92361b9880d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2369463d8ede9e477cfaf832815ef3c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1561937403235278917e112e7843f5b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3117b3a03ff471f00f67b26aade3e091&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77680239477915203c692473a1450584&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9bcca043358a8f1b8a9a2999a79a6f6</data>
