<edge source="Russia" target="North Korea">
  <data key="d8">12.0</data>
  <data key="d9">North Korea-Russia relations have deepened significantly through extensive military cooperation, particularly in the context of Russia’s war in Ukraine. Since early autumn, North Korea has deployed between 10,000 and 14,000 military personnel to Russia, with some reports indicating a total of up to 14,000 soldiers sent in 2024 alone, many of whom have fought alongside Russian forces on the frontlines, gaining practical combat experience. These troops are reportedly mobilized from North Korea’s youth population, whose participation is ideologically framed by Pyongyang as defending national honor, with official messaging characterizing them as “bombs and flames.” 

In parallel, North Korea has supplied Russia with substantial military matériel, including over 33,000 containers of artillery shells and weapon systems, marking a significant escalation after a prior decline in shipments. In return, North Korea seeks advanced Russian technologies, notably in spy satellite systems and nuclear weapons development. Russia has reciprocated by providing North Korea with trophy equipment for exhibition at memorial events, symbolizing mutual military solidarity. This cooperation is further underscored symbolically by the joint display of North Korean and Russian flags in parades, reflecting a strategic and ideological alignment. The exchange represents a mutually beneficial arrangement: North Korea gains critical military technology and political backing, while Russia offsets its own manpower and munitions shortages through Pyongyang’s direct combat contributions and logistical support.&lt;SEP&gt;Russia's influence led North Korea to become a production base, contributing to improved conditions there.</data>
  <data key="d10">alliance,arms shipment,arms transfer,combat experience,cooperation,economic dependency,equipment transfer,flag display,ideological alignment,military alliance,military cooperation,military deployment,military supply,production base,propaganda,strategic alliance,support,symbolic display,technology exchange,troop transfer</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-214c05e5837b1920019322b383e38e60&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b39d28f897b28fac29f3bb283dd59119&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f539231f0337d24e0f7782691b6fac00&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-939a2cfef1695d968a321a56df325c53&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2cd9eaecb1b87407745fb11b4c0a1b5a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-22bf377cf0305c3d3989c37e5d3450cd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-dc8a59662338ae99506795bdf8f3e570&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bea54a7e2da99c4d21fe120e09b5930&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c7c66fd004b5169922bcb617129ac236&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-182d3ae7e14d1083d21cb4dce15639d9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b081d06450863ed7e420f49361e136e9</data>
  <data key="d12">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Корея\3.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Корея\5.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Корея\13.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Корея\15.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Корея\21.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Корея\24.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Корея\25.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Корея\26.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Корея\37.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Корея\39.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Корея\27.txt</data>
  <data key="d13">1778011292</data>
