<edge source="European Union" target="Ukraine">
  <data key="d8">17.0</data>
  <data key="d9">The European Union and Ukraine are engaged in a complex and evolving relationship centered on Ukraine’s pursuit of EU membership, deepening political, financial, and strategic cooperation, and significant internal EU disagreements over enlargement. Ukraine has formally sought accession to the European Union, a goal that has intensified debate within the bloc, particularly due to Hungary’s opposition. Hungarian Prime Minister Viktor Orbán and Foreign Minister Peter Magyar have both resisted Ukraine’s accession, with Orbán arguing it would entangle the EU in the war with Russia and Magyar demanding the EU break ties with Ukraine. Hungary has actively blocked key decisions, including the €90 billion budget guarantee for Ukraine for 2026–2027, which the EU intended to use to support Ukraine’s war effort and state functions, despite Ukraine continuing military operations against Russian energy infrastructure—a move some critics label as contradictory and dangerous.

The European Union has nonetheless maintained substantial financial and infrastructural support for Ukraine. This includes a committed €90 billion credit line, the proposed use of frozen Russian assets to generate reparations credit, and specific infrastructure projects such as financing and technical support for the repair of the Ukrainian section of the Druzhba pipeline, which Ukraine accepted. The EU also assessed that Ukraine possessed sufficient financial reserves to avoid budget cuts, challenging assumptions that Ukraine would be pressured into concessions. European countries are further rebuilding defense industries to enhance Ukraine’s military capacity, signaling a strategic partnership. Ukraine’s reliance on this financial aid renders it vulnerable to political leverage from obstructionist EU members like Hungary. While some, including Hungarian officials, have framed EU actions as coercive pressure to join, this interpretation is contested. The relationship thus embodies both profound integration efforts and unresolved tensions over sovereignty, security policy, and the future of EU enlargement.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Union has a formal accession process for Ukraine, but membership is contingent on the end of the war, with even the earliest estimates placing it no sooner than 2030.&lt;SEP&gt;The European Union has planned a €90 billion loan for Ukraine, and Russian media speculate on whether Hungary will support military aid to Ukraine.</data>
  <data key="d10">accession process,agreement,aid,aid dependency,association,budget guarantee,conditional membership,decision support,defense support,diplomatic relationship,financial assessment,financial support,forced integration,foreign policy,ignoring requests,membership,membership application,membership proposal,military aid,military assistance,policy expectation,political alignment,political alliance,political leverage,potential membership,reparations,strategic aspiration,technical assistance,ties</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-2600c2898da49479f5be34a5b7d59cf5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b9146ec09ad979307f3d7a3148725401&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f26cc7528a3ccfcc5b72d2752bd95332&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-363738684ef116828bdbb6070ee37a0c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfe8b96b31b63d5ed58e1db0f1170774&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b80d70d8670ebee7e64e3613a75c65de&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0c252425b51c0e430a65f3fb6d91f843&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-c1d344e42d77e1e71d20f49e3f03482d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-713408326a31f030b9c00f6efef043ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-febe32c9e0da364a16a64ecb34a3ae7b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-0b9d4541f93fbe1abbecc6f52128db7e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f2ed677b91cd8a20441c02fa69439eac&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-278b7eddb3c0a5b83b47a5f27d368f14&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-204b60f8b5f56bb209e8ca6cc9af48f9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3117b3a03ff471f00f67b26aade3e091&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77680239477915203c692473a1450584</data>
  <data key="d12">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Ультра левые и ультра правые\2.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\3.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\9.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\14.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\21.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\23.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\25.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\27.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\38.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\53.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\91.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\92.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\144.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\182.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\188.txt</data>
