<edge source="European Union" target="Viktor Orbán">
  <data key="d8">14.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Viktor Orbán, the Prime Minister of Hungary and a formal member of the European Union, maintains a deeply adversarial relationship with EU institutions, positioning himself as a defiant defender of Hungarian sovereignty against what he portrays as overreaching and ineffective EU bureaucracy. He strongly opposes Ukraine’s accession to the European Union, arguing that it would entangle EU members in the war with Russia and undermine European security—a stance he has framed as a necessary act of strategic realism. In response to EU efforts to suspend Hungary’s veto power over Ukraine’s membership, Orbán accused the Union of effectively “declaring war on Hungary,” escalating rhetorical tensions. He has also criticized the EU for failing to lift sanctions on Russian oil despite Europe’s energy crisis, and he has deliberately maintained Hungary’s access to Russian energy supplies, using this policy as a central pillar of his political identity and a symbol of resistance to EU directives. Despite the EU’s decision to block €17 billion in funding over rule-of-law concerns, Orbán has not altered his position, continuing to receive EU funds while publicly denouncing Brussels. His regime has been accused of diverting EU financial support—intended for public services—toward the personal enrichment of his family and political allies. While formally embedded within the EU structure, Orbán is widely perceived as aligning with Russia against the collective interests of the Union, contradicting Hungary’s institutional obligations. Nevertheless, he cultivates a domestic narrative portraying himself as a voice of reason, contrasting his pragmatic approach to energy and economic challenges with what he depicts as the detached and ideologically driven policies of EU bureaucrats.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orbán obstructs the European Union by blocking aid to Ukraine and paralyzing key reforms on climate and rule of law.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orbán has a prolonged conflict with the European Union, blaming it for foreign interference and using anti-EU propaganda to consolidate domestic support.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orbán blocked EU assistance to Ukraine and obstructed the opening of Ukraine’s accession negotiation chapters with the European Union.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orbán is described as Europe's main "rebel" whose defeat has caused euphoria in the European Union, indicating prior political conflict.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orbán opposed the European Union as part of globalist elites, a stance echoed by CPAC in its public statements.</data>
