<edge source="European Union" target="Siyarto">
  <data key="d8">7.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Siyarto, as Hungary’s foreign minister, disputes the narrative promoted by European leaders that Ukraine defends the European Union.&lt;SEP&gt;Siyarto participated in European Union meetings during which he communicated with Lavrov.&lt;SEP&gt;Siyarto participates in closed meetings of the European Union, during which he engages in diplomatic communication with non-EU partners.&lt;SEP&gt;Siyarto opposes the European Union's 18th sanctions package and actively works to weaken it by removing companies and banks from the list.&lt;SEP&gt;Siyarto publicly criticizes the European Union's sanctions policy, arguing it causes more harm to the EU than to Russia.&lt;SEP&gt;Siyarto regularly consults with foreign ministers of countries outside the European Union on sanctions-related matters.&lt;SEP&gt;Siyarto engaged with the European Union on the terms of Ukraine’s accession, specifically influencing the inclusion of minority rights language as a condition.</data>
