<edge source="European Union" target="Slovakia">
  <data key="d8">6.0</data>
  <data key="d9">The European Union proposed a fact-finding mission to Ukraine, which Slovakia supported and advocated to include Slovak representatives.&lt;SEP&gt;Slovakia refuses to support the 20th package of sanctions proposed by the European Union.&lt;SEP&gt;Slovakia, along with Hungary, delayed the voting on the 18th sanctions package and demands an exemption to continue purchasing Russian gas and oil.&lt;SEP&gt;Slovakia collaborated with Hungary to pressure the European Union into lifting sanctions against Russian individuals, often initiating negotiations with lists of names requested by Russia.&lt;SEP&gt;Slovakia is internally divided over compliance with EU sanctions against Russia, with Robert Fico’s actions creating uncertainty about its alignment.&lt;SEP&gt;Slovakia, as a member of the European Union, is willing to share its experience in Euro-integration with Ukraine.</data>
  <data key="d10">Euro-integration experience,delay,diplomatic engagement,internal division,lobbying,policy disagreement,sanction opposition,sanctions compliance,sanctions exemption request,sanctions opposition</data>
