<edge source="European Union" target="United Kingdom">
  <data key="d8">3.0</data>
  <data key="d9">The European Union has previously required a £2 billion contribution from the United Kingdom for SAFE membership, a condition that has since become less rigid due to changing geopolitical dynamics.&lt;SEP&gt;The United Kingdom is negotiating with the European Union to reach a defense agreement prior to the May summit, despite prior failed attempts to join SAFE.&lt;SEP&gt;Negotiations for the United Kingdom’s accession to the SAFE fund failed in November due to the European Union’s requirement of a £2 billion entry fee.</data>
  <data key="d10">defense agreement,defense integration,diplomatic negotiation,failed negotiation,financial contribution,financial demand</data>
