<edge source="Ukraine" target="NATO">
  <data key="d8">4.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Ukraine is receiving support from NATO to enhance its defense capabilities and resist Russian military advances, as Russia perceives NATO’s assistance as a threat.&lt;SEP&gt;NATO aircraft operate near Ukraine, detecting Russian emissions and providing targeting data to Ukrainian forces without entering Ukrainian airspace.&lt;SEP&gt;Ukrainian forces use NATO signals intelligence to locate and destroy Russian radar and air defense systems with drones.&lt;SEP&gt;Ukraine was considered for potential membership in NATO, a prospect that Russia viewed as a direct threat.</data>
  <data key="d10">defense partnership,electronic surveillance,electronic targeting,intelligence support,military support,potential membership,strategic aspiration,tactical coordination</data>
