<edge source="NATO" target="Hungary">
  <data key="d8">4.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Hungary is a member of NATO but its foreign minister actively undermined NATO-aligned EU decisions by sharing sensitive information with Russia.&lt;SEP&gt;Hungary is a member of NATO but is targeted by Russian intelligence as an operational field, indicating a strategic contradiction between its formal alliances and its perceived vulnerability to external influence.&lt;SEP&gt;Hungary remains a member of NATO, with public support for membership comparable to that for the European Union, indicating a strong national identity aligned with the West.&lt;SEP&gt;NATO limited Hungary’s access to sensitive intelligence in 2024, reflecting growing distrust of Hungary’s alignment with Russia.</data>
  <data key="d10">geopolitical target,intelligence restriction,member state,membership,public support,security contradiction</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-8fa6adba441e776b293e92361b9880d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e4089c9c991c6402b317d88ca6848ab9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de92df91fd68b8019a5e2c98e87d545e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a810084503e65cb067ff1fc3c7a05189</data>
