<edge source="Kremlin" target="Hungary">
  <data key="d8">4.0</data>
  <data key="d9">The Kremlin considers Hungary part of its sphere of influence and is actively working to ensure Viktor Orbán remains in power to block EU decisions and extend Russian influence.&lt;SEP&gt;The Kremlin engaged in political interference in Hungary through bot-driven disinformation campaigns in Russian-language Telegram channels, aiming to sway public opinion in favor of Viktor Orbán.&lt;SEP&gt;The Kremlin’s attack on the pipeline and Hungary’s subsequent blocking of EU aid indicate a mutual interest in preserving Russian energy flows to Hungary.&lt;SEP&gt;Hungarian state media promoted disinformation narratives aligned with Kremlin propaganda, suggesting Moscow advisers were involved in fabricating claims about Ukrainian and opposition plots.</data>
  <data key="d10">energy cooperation,geopolitical control,influence,interference,mutual interest,political influence,propaganda collaboration,sphere of influence</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-583ccb318ed3bd5eb71b569940315d4f&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a865b7c03998478f1296272dd37b2e83&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-278b7eddb3c0a5b83b47a5f27d368f14&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3e4bedfc173098465d955c0364c5de9b</data>
