  <data key="d13">1777937114</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Kremlin" target="Sándor Pintér">
  <data key="d8">1.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Sándor Pintér transmitted confidential EU information to the Kremlin during breaks in EU Council meetings, reportedly calling from the restroom and reporting like a subordinate to Sergey Lavrov.</data>
  <data key="d10">coordination,espionage,information leak</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-a55a1b2f7d86f155201f7562a7195495</data>
  <data key="d12">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\101.txt</data>
  <data key="d13">1777934335</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Kremlin" target="Viktor Orbán">
  <data key="d8">6.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Viktor Orbán is alleged to be working directly for the Kremlin, with his government’s actions-including information leaks-aligned with Russian strategic interests.&lt;SEP&gt;The Kremlin deployed bots in Russian-language Telegram channels to promote Viktor Orbán and criticize his political opponent, Péter Márki-Zay, as part of a coordinated disinformation campaign.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orbán is regarded by the Kremlin not as an ally but as a disposable technical instrument of influence, comparable to past Warsaw Pact leaders, with his position subject to manipulation or replacement.&lt;SEP&gt;Viktor Orbán cultivated a close personal and political relationship with the Kremlin, receiving direct communication from Vladimir Putin and engaging in undisclosed discussions later exposed by surveillance.&lt;SEP&gt;The Kremlin issued direct orders to Viktor Orbán, who executed them, demonstrating a relationship of subordination rather than independent foreign policy.&lt;SEP&gt;The Kremlin cultivated a political alliance with Viktor Orbán, using leaked recordings of their conversations as leverage against other Eastern European leaders.</data>
  <data key="d10">alignment,bot campaign,command and control,communication leverage,disinformation,influence,instrument of influence,personal contact,political alliance,political collaboration,strategic cooperation,subordination,support</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-a55a1b2f7d86f155201f7562a7195495&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a865b7c03998478f1296272dd37b2e83&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fa6adba441e776b293e92361b9880d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de92df91fd68b8019a5e2c98e87d545e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3117b3a03ff471f00f67b26aade3e091&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9bcca043358a8f1b8a9a2999a79a6f6</data>
  <data key="d12">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\101.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\104.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\182.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\198.txt</data>
  <data key="d13">1777938052</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Kremlin" target="Robert Fico">
  <data key="d8">4.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Robert Fico is alleged to be working for the Kremlin, with his political maneuvers in Slovakia coordinated to advance Russian interests through party manipulation.&lt;SEP&gt;Robert Fico previously relied on the Kremlin for political protection but now lacks confidence in its ability to safeguard his position after Orban’s loss.&lt;SEP&gt;The Kremlin is exerting strategic pressure on Robert Fico to assume Orbán’s role as a pro-Russian blocker within the EU, despite Fico’s political vulnerabilities.&lt;SEP&gt;Robert Fico is attempting to visit the Kremlin, signaling a pro-Russian political alignment despite domestic and international backlash.</data>
  <data key="d10">alignment,lose confidence in,political alignment,political collaboration,political influence,pro-Russian orientation,rely on,strategic pressure,visit</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-a55a1b2f7d86f155201f7562a7195495&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-09de750ab096b64385f95a95c7d0e5ad&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e9bcca043358a8f1b8a9a2999a79a6f6</data>
  <data key="d12">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\101.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\190.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\198.txt</data>
  <data key="d13">1777938052</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Kremlin" target="Petr Pellegrini">
  <data key="d8">1.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Petr Pellegrini and his party Hlas were allegedly created as a Kremlin-backed project to split opposition votes in Slovakia and ensure SMER’s electoral victory.</data>
  <data key="d10">creation,political manipulation</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-a55a1b2f7d86f155201f7562a7195495</data>
  <data key="d12">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\101.txt</data>
