<edge source="Slovakia" target="Hungary">
  <data key="d8">7.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Hungary, under Orbán, positions itself as aligned with Slovakia under Robert Fico to create an illusion of broader regional support for its anti-Ukrainian policies.&lt;SEP&gt;Hungary provides fighter jet support to defend Slovak airspace following the transfer of MiG-29s to Ukraine.&lt;SEP&gt;Hungary and Slovakia both depend on oil transit via the Friendship pipeline, and Hungary links their shared interest to its blockade of EU sanctions.&lt;SEP&gt;Hungary and Slovakia jointly supported a fact-finding mission to Ukraine and shared a stance of denying technical damage to the Druzhba pipeline.&lt;SEP&gt;Hungary, through its foreign minister, coordinated with the Kremlin to interfere in Slovak elections by supporting SMER and attempting to ensure Danko’s parliamentary entry.&lt;SEP&gt;Hungary and Slovakia jointly coordinated efforts to block or delay EU sanctions and submitted joint proposals for removing Russian individuals from sanctions lists.&lt;SEP&gt;Slovakia’s border proximity to Hungary enabled cross-border criminal movement and coordination between Ukrainian/Russian groups operating in both countries.</data>
  <data key="d10">air defense support,blockade,coordination,cross-border criminal activity,diplomatic alignment,electoral manipulation,geographic proximity,military cooperation,political alignment,political interference,shared interest,transit dependency</data>
