<edge source="Hungary" target="Fidesz">
  <data key="d8">9.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Fidesz is the ruling political party in Hungary, led by Prime Minister Viktor Orbán, and has maintained control over the country’s political institutions for over 16 years. Through a strategy of institutional capture, Fidesz has systematically consolidated power by dominating the media, influencing the judiciary, controlling intelligence agencies, and manipulating electoral boundaries. Hungary’s legal framework, shaped by Fidesz’s parliamentary supermajority, enables the party to alter electoral laws and district demarcations, ensuring disproportionate parliamentary representation despite near-equal vote shares. This structural dominance has facilitated unprecedented electoral manipulation, including allegations of vote-buying, coercion of voters in impoverished regions, and exploitation of social vulnerability through financial incentives and threats. In past elections, Fidesz achieved vote shares of 80–100% in certain constituencies, attributed to systematic electoral fraud. The party has also engaged in disinformation campaigns, publishing AI-generated content targeting Ukraine and promoting Orbán’s political agenda domestically. While Fidesz faces unprecedented electoral challenges ahead of the upcoming parliamentary vote, its entrenched control over state apparatuses continues to define Hungary’s democratic trajectory.&lt;SEP&gt;Fidesz, led by Orbán, lost the 2026 Hungarian elections, ending its hold on power.</data>
  <data key="d10">coercion,electoral defeat,electoral dominance,electoral manipulation,governance_system,governing authority,governing party,institutional control,legal manipulation,media dissemination,national context,political leadership,propaganda,ruling_party,systemic fraud,voter bribery</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-bae0e37e11b33519772a72128c43c6ee&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-26fcbf6510a404d136a66a46e0584357&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a3aab01d8a12e8135d55b3153fc006d0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8fa6adba441e776b293e92361b9880d1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-95251bcfc4d08a0a36c341b9a9e2da54&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-867b81690ecba5bc75830acd44c39131&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-a810084503e65cb067ff1fc3c7a05189</data>
