<edge source="Hungary" target="Viktor Orbán">
  <data key="d8">17.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Viktor Orbán is the Prime Minister of Hungary and the long-serving political leader of the Fidesz party, having held power for over 16 years. He governs a country where democratic institutions have significantly deteriorated under his rule, with the rule of law at its lowest level in the European Union. Orbán has systematically consolidated control over state institutions, the media, and the judiciary, dismantling checks and balances while enriching his inner circle—actions widely criticized as authoritarian drift and erosion of democratic norms. He frames his leadership as essential to safeguarding Hungary’s sovereignty, national identity, and cultural integrity, portraying the European Union and NATO as hostile forces threatening Hungarian interests. This narrative is reinforced through a sustained disinformation campaign that positions him as the sole protector of the nation against external control.

Orbán’s foreign policy has drawn intense scrutiny, particularly his close ties with Vladimir Putin and Russia, which he justifies as vital for Hungary’s energy security, low fuel prices, and cultural preservation. His decision to cease diesel fuel exports to Ukraine has been interpreted as aligning Hungary’s interests with Moscow, sparking domestic protests and international criticism that his policies subordinate Hungarian sovereignty to Russian influence. Despite this, he has received praise from figures such as Donald Trump and Donald Trump Jr., who laud him as a champion of national independence and traditional values. Orbán also promotes domestic policies focused on economic development, job creation, trade expansion, curbing illegal immigration, and ensuring law and order.

While he is celebrated by supporters as a defender of Hungarian autonomy, his leadership is also the central event analyzed in Russian media, particularly in the context of his potential political defeat. Protesters within Hungary have demonstrated against his pro-Moscow stance and the perceived corruption of his administration. The conflicting portrayals of Orbán—as both a national savior and an authoritarian autocrat—reflect deep domestic and international divisions over the trajectory of Hungary’s democracy and its place in the Western alliance.</data>
  <data key="d10">authoritarianism,electoral strategy,governance,institutional erosion,leadership,national representation,policy decision,policy resistance,political leadership,political narrative,political opposition,political representation,power_consolidation,public deception,sovereignty</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-8f6038412dae5ce5c36860aae0893cce&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2886b7cb500c955cf1d8671ed22bd946&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3960e17c128f750dfd948945c91a00ff&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-443c22f60ed93ec379e718efa356a140&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-02f8127f57647c6f52ac2f580f293f65&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-84d9d2605d4824a81c0829b9eb92d7b6&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-49d9496e943d94ccc071cf105396b990&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-de92df91fd68b8019a5e2c98e87d545e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fc1feb8e698e39594612de628b9b30f8&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2843e721f5be37e2778dd3123cdcec43&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-1561937403235278917e112e7843f5b0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-89e09c599b4678441dbd4c330f5e7aa1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2c3129b97ce4bf590efeb8acc86b772e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e5ab60c301522fe44f5b6ce532a3c05b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3f9c193424dde3d5eaae9c7403580444&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-77680239477915203c692473a1450584&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-4219648b35dcbd430c607633467c92dc</data>
  <data key="d12">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\20.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\30.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\59.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\80.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\131.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\133.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\142.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\147.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\148.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\151.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\163.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\188.txt&lt;SEP&gt;D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\189.txt</data>
