<edge source="Hungary" target="Soviet Union">
  <data key="d8">3.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Hungary is now treated by Russia as an operational field in the same manner as Soviet-era targets in Latin America and Africa, demonstrating continuity in Russia’s use of active measures across decades.&lt;SEP&gt;The Soviet Union is historically linked to Hungary through its violent suppression of the Hungarian Uprising in 1956, an event referenced by protesters to symbolize resistance to external influence.&lt;SEP&gt;The Soviet Union invaded Hungary in 1956 with tanks, establishing a historical precedent for Russian coercive influence in Budapest.</data>
  <data key="d10">historical conflict,historical influence,historical precedent,military intervention,operational continuity</data>
