<edge source="Viktor Orbán" target="Michael Naki">
  <data key="d8">1.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Michael Naki critiques Viktor Orbán’s political strategy by comparing him to a mouse in a fable, arguing that Orbán’s value to Moscow is contingent solely on his ability to undermine European unity, and that his power will vanish once he loses it.</data>
  <data key="d10">analogy,political critique</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-de92df91fd68b8019a5e2c98e87d545e</data>
  <data key="d12">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\140.txt</data>
