<edge source="Fidesz" target="2026 Hungarian Elections">
  <data key="d8">3.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Fidesz redrew electoral district boundaries for the 2026 Hungarian Elections to eliminate opposition strongholds and create new districts favorable to its party.&lt;SEP&gt;Fidesz, under Orbán’s leadership, redrew electoral district boundaries before the 2026 elections to eliminate two opposition strongholds, enhancing its electoral advantage.&lt;SEP&gt;Fidesz is a major participant in the 2026 Hungarian Elections, seeking to retain power despite strong polling opposition from Tisza.</data>
  <data key="d10">boundary redrawing,electoral competition,electoral manipulation,electoral reform,gerrymandering,participation</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-2369463d8ede9e477cfaf832815ef3c5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-b6bcd039eb9ab628a1ffb566a855dd2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-867b81690ecba5bc75830acd44c39131</data>
