  <data key="d13">1777936763</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Fidesz" target="2022 Hungarian Elections">
  <data key="d8">2.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Fidesz won 88 of 106 districts in the 2022 Hungarian Elections and used the compensation rule to convert 54% of the popular vote into 135 parliamentary seats, achieving a constitutional supermajority.&lt;SEP&gt;Fidesz achieved overwhelming electoral success in the 2022 Hungarian elections, winning most parliamentary seats and reinforcing Orbán’s control.</data>
  <data key="d10">electoral advantage,electoral victory,power consolidation,supermajority</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-b6bcd039eb9ab628a1ffb566a855dd2b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-867b81690ecba5bc75830acd44c39131</data>
  <data key="d12">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\142.txt</data>
  <data key="d13">1777936764</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Fidesz" target="Budapest">
  <data key="d8">1.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Fidesz eliminated two districts in Budapest to reduce opposition influence, despite Budapest being a stronghold of opposition voting.</data>
  <data key="d10">electoral manipulation,gerrymandering</data>
