  <data key="d14"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Igor Koryol" target="Semyon Mogilevich">
  <data key="d8">1.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Igor Koryol operated under the influence and authority of Semyon Mogilevich, who mediated disputes and maintained control over criminal networks, though no direct payment for protection was confirmed.</data>
  <data key="d10">criminal hierarchy,influence,protection</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-b107034176b638d6ed0508c3346f0725</data>
  <data key="d12">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\134.txt</data>
  <data key="d13">1777936129</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Igor Koryol" target="Leonid Stitsyura">
  <data key="d8">1.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Igor Koryol and Leonid Stitsyura led the two dominant Ukrainian criminal brigades in Budapest, jointly controlling entertainment venues, nightclubs, and restaurants through protection rackets.</data>
  <data key="d10">criminal alliance,territorial control</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-b107034176b638d6ed0508c3346f0725</data>
  <data key="d12">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\134.txt</data>
  <data key="d13">1777936129</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Igor Koryol" target="Goldf Gim">
  <data key="d8">1.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Igor Koryol was first encountered by the translator at Goldf Gim, a gym in Budapest, where their initial relationship began.</data>
  <data key="d10">association,meeting place</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-b107034176b638d6ed0508c3346f0725</data>
  <data key="d12">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\134.txt</data>
  <data key="d13">1777936130</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Igor Koryol" target="Black Skull">
  <data key="d8">1.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Leadership of the Black Skull criminal group was transferred to Igor Koryol in the late 1980s, marking the beginning of his dominance in Budapest’s underworld.</data>
  <data key="d10">leadership transition</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-b107034176b638d6ed0508c3346f0725</data>
  <data key="d12">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\134.txt</data>
  <data key="d13">1777936130</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Igor Koryol" target="Dietmar Klaud">
  <data key="d8">1.0</data>
  <data key="d9">Dietmar Klaud received money deliveries from the speaker through Igor Koryol’s arrangement, indicating a trusted intermediary relationship.</data>
  <data key="d10">association,money transfer</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-c338d5794d84977817897ee6bca1756e</data>
  <data key="d12">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\134.txt</data>
  <data key="d13">1777936138</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Igor Koryol" target="Alexander Kirichenko">
  <data key="d8">1.0</data>
  <data key="d9">The speaker had a falling out with Igor Koryol involving Alexander Kirichenko and the speaker’s childhood home, linked to a Ukrainian city mayor.</data>
  <data key="d10">conflict,personal dispute</data>
  <data key="d11">chunk-c338d5794d84977817897ee6bca1756e</data>
  <data key="d12">D:\ObsidianWiki\GeoSpoiler-RAG\output\normalized\Венгрия Словакия\134.txt</data>
  <data key="d13">1777936138</data>
  <data key="d14"></data>
</edge>
<edge source="Igor Koryol" target="Mogilevich">
  <data key="d8">1.0</data>
  <data key="d9">The speaker claims to have heard Igor Koryol speaking with Mogilevich but had no direct contact with Mogilevich himself.</data>
